video_title: kung fu panda 4  official trailer
description:
kung fu panda 4  in theaters march 8

this spring for the first time in almost a decade comedy icon jack black returns to his role as po the worlds most unlikely kung fu master with a hilarious buttkicking new chapter in dreamworks animations beloved actioncomedy franchise kung fu panda 4 

after three deathdefying adventures defeating worldclass villains with his unmatched courage and mad martial arts skills po the dragon warrior golden globe nominee jack black is called upon by destiny to  give it a rest already more specifically hes tapped to become the spiritual leader of the valley of peace

that poses a couple of obvious problems first po knows as much about spiritual leadership as he does about the paleo diet and second he needs to quickly find and train a new dragon warrior before he can assume his new lofty position 

even worse theres been a recent sighting of a wicked powerful sorceress chameleon oscar winner viola davis a tiny lizard who can shapeshift into any creature large or small and chameleon has her greedy beady little eyes on pos staff of wisdom which would give her the power to resummon all the master villains whom po has vanquished to the spirit realm 

so pos going to need some help he finds it kinda in the form of crafty quickwitted thief zhen golden globe winner awkwafina a corsac fox who really gets under pos fur but whose skills will prove invaluable in their quest to protect the valley of peace from chameleons reptilian claws this comedic oddcouple duo will have to work together in the process po will discover that heroes can be found in the most unexpected places 

the film features the voice talent of returning stars academy award winner dustin hoffman as kung fu master shifu james hong everything everywhere all at once as pos adoptive father mr ping academy award nominee bryan cranston as pos birth father li and emmy award nominee ian mcshane as tai lung shifus former student and archnemesis oscar winner ke huy quan everything everywhere all at once joins the ensemble as a new character han the leader of the den of thieves 
 
kung fu panda 4 is directed by mike mitchell dreamworks animations trolls shrek forever after and produced by rebecca huntley dreamworks animations the bad guys the films codirector is stephanie ma stine shera and the princesses of power in 2008 the academy awardnominated 2008 inaugural chapter kung fu panda became dreamworks animations highestgrossing original animated film and launched a franchise that has earned more than 18 billion at the global boxoffice

video_title: dune part two  official trailer 3
tags: Action,Arrakis,Arrival,Atreides,Austin Butler,Bene Gesserit,Coming Soon,Denis Villeneuve,Dune,Dune Sequel,Dune: Part Two,Enemy,Film,Film Trailer,Florence Pugh,Frank Herbert,Fremen,Harkonnen,Jason Momoa,Javier Bardem,Josh Brolin,Kevin J Anderson,Legendary,Movie,New Movie 2024,Official Trailer,Paul Atreides,Rebecca Ferguson,Sandworm,Sci-Fi,Stellan Skarsgard,Timothee Chalamet,Trailer,Trailer 2023,WB,Warner,Warner Bros,Warner Brothers,Zendaya
description:
you are not prepared for what is to come duneparttwo  only in theaters march 1

the saga continues as awardwinning filmmaker denis villeneuve embarks on dune part two the next chapter of frank herberts celebrated novel dune with an expanded allstar international ensemble cast the film from warner bros pictures and legendary pictures is the highly anticipated followup to 2021s sixtime academy awardwinning dune

the bigscreen epic continues the adaptation of frank herberts acclaimed bestseller dune with returning and new stars including oscar nominee timothe chalamet wonka call me by your name zendaya spiderman no way home malcolm  marie euphoria rebecca ferguson mission impossible  dead reckoning oscar nominee josh brolin avengers end game milk oscar nominee austin butler elvis once upon a timein hollywood oscar nominee florence pugh black widow little women dave bautista the guardians of the galaxy films thor love and thunder oscar winner christopher walken the deer hunter hairspray la seydoux the james bond franchise and crimes of the future souheila yacoub the braves climax with stellan skarsgrd the mamma mia films avengers age of ultron with oscar nominee charlotte rampling 45 years assassins creed and oscar winner javier bardem no country for old men being the ricardos

dune part two will explore the mythic journey of paul atreides as he unites with chani and the fremen while on a path of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the known universe he endeavors to prevent a terrible future only he can foresee

villeneuve directed from a screenplay he cowrote with jon spaihts based on herberts novel the film is produced by mary parent cale boyter villeneuve tanya lapointe and patrick mccormick the executive producers are joshua grode herbert w gains jon spaihts thomas tull brian herbert byron merritt kim herbert with kevin j anderson serving as creative consultant

villeneuve is again collaborating with his dune creatives oscarwinning director of photography greig fraser oscarwinning production designer patrice vermette oscarwinning editor joe walker oscarwinning visual effects supervisor paul lambert oscarnominated costume designer jacqueline west oscarwinning composer hans zimmer is again on hand to create the score

warner bros pictures and legendary pictures present a legendary pictures production a film by denis villeneuve dune part two the film is slated for a march 1 2024 release in theaters and imax nationwide and internationally beginning on 28 february 2024 distributed by warner bros pictures

video_title: laufey tiny desk concert
tags: NPR,NPR Music,National Public Radio,Live,Performance,tiny desk,tiny desk concert,tony desk,tiny concert
description:
ashley pointer  december 13 2023
i grew up playing classical music and its so special to get to play my songs almost in this chamberlike setting laufey says in her performance accompanied by a string quartet the singersongwriters modern jazzpop love songs soared at the tiny desk the intimacy of our little corner only heightened its impact

laufeys music undeniably bridges the gap between jazz and younger mainstream audiences coming to the genre her sophomore album bewitched broke spotifys alltime streaming record for a jazz debut ever in the platforms history and resulted in her first grammy nomination she opens the set with from the start a bouncy whimsical tune about unrequited love with a friend connecting chet bakerlike scats with charming and playful lyrics taking a more melancholic turn into 2021s let you break my heart again and promise her velvety vocals rich with vulnerability dance elegantly with the strings creating a symphony of emotions laufey concludes the set with california and me which she explains was heavily influenced by her receiving her first baby grand and compositions by liszt and chopin this mesmerizing performance is a captivating testament to the power of collaboration and musics ability to evoke raw unfiltered emotion

video_title: its adoption day finalization
tags: della vlogs,della,dallin and bella,dallin lambert,bella lambert,della vlogs prank,youtube shorts,vlog channel,couple channel,dallin and bella lambert,origami owl,lambert,weems,della bella dallin,della shorts,della vlogs video
description:
if some of you are confused on the title this below explains a little better 
december 4th will forever be one of the best days of our lives 

an adoption is finalized when all of the necessary postplacement requirements have been met when people ask when does the adoption become final for the adopting parents in most adoptions the final adoption hearing occurs around six months after placement although some hearings can happen as little as three months or up to a year after placement

traditionally adoption finalization occurs in a courtroom although more and more judges are offering final adoption hearings over videocall or phone call your adoption specialist and adoption attorney will work together to schedule this hearing and ensure you are prepared for any questions that may be asked during this process

we love you all so much
dallin and bella

dellavlogs

top_comments:
mahomes was yelling at the wrong guy  he should direct his anger at toney a pro who should know better
upset over a blatant penalty man if mahomes reacted like this over that imagine how he would have reacted if the chiefs got the same treatment the bills got in the bills eagles game refs totally screwed them
after looking at the replay our guy clearly lined up offsides the refs had to call it same type of dumbass move that we did in the afc championship several years ago when one of you defensive players lined up off side when we intercepted brady to nullify the play and lose the game mahomes needs to aim his anger in the right direction  his own man we deserved to lose and will cont to do so with this lousy offense too bad  wasting a very good defense this year
just a straight up fair amd square loss for the chiefs unfortunately they had an offsides that seemingly cost them the win or atleast lead really unprofessional and pathetic that your starting quarterback has a temper tantrum on the sidelines yelling at the refs for doing their jobs well
the chiefs had their chances to win and they didnt get it done
classic man gets so many calls his way over the years gets a few called against him and he has an aneurism
all i have to say is that chiefs fans got a little taste of what its like to be a bills fan for the last 30 years
legend has it that mahomes is still screaming on the sideline
via adam schefter on twitter

chiefs hc andy reid was not pleased that officials did not warn him that kadarius toney was lined up offsides the way they have in the past about the call the normally mildmannered reid said its a bit embarrassing for the national football league for that to take place
i get great joy from seeing the refs treat the chiefs like every other team in the league
this was amazing to see about time the refs make the correct call and stop making these calls for mahomes
to be honest there was still over a minute and the bills had timeouts to score a td no guarantee that offsides call not being called would have meant a chiefs win
ironic patrick mahomes and chiefs fans realizing what every other team has to go through when facing the chiefs
i want to watch a football game not a every time kelsie catches the ball we have to cut to taylor swifts reaction
there is absolutely a major problem with officials tainting games with either questionable calls or non calls  and completely subjective  penalties which on some occasions determines the outcome of the game 

this wasnt one of them even stevie wonder can see toney was way offsides here
no amount of cursing and yelling can deflect from the fact that they lost mahomes just made himself look like a spoiled unsportsman like loser
as a chiefs fan im embarrassed and mortified by the behavoir mahomes displayed it shows how badly winning has gone to his head and how inflated his ego is that he cant handle losing with some ounch of dignity even if he thought someone else was in the wrong
watched them take 3 games from us in the past cuz of calls like these i still remember a game were mahomes got intercepted 4 times and they all came back theyve been spoiled for too long now they think they should let little mistakes like these slide
i love how patrick mahomes can throw a tantrum in front of the world but when i do it at work i need to grow up 
chiefs right now are in a classic post superbowl era after winning were gonna go through some tough struggles mainly with our receivers but hopefully we still stay strong and are alright going forward

video_title: the day before disaster sets a dangerous precedent
tags: the day before,scam,scam game,asset flip,fntastic
description:
the day before launched 4 days ago and proved to be a monumental failure  so much so that the studio shutdown and is likely running with the money

special thanks to bigfrytv for his gameplay
hollyrexs clip httpswwwtwitchtvhollyrexclipbombastichyperalmonditsboshytimeyk9mhvw17bk6cm
top_comments:
steam has taken the game down  you can no longer buy it  apparently steam also holds money for 30 days  theyre also allowing refunds no matter how long you have played  so it looks like the developers jumped ship too early
luckily steam is accepting refunds for players past the 2 hour mark this was too much of a scam even for steam
players and valve should put these guys in court
one thing i have learned over the years is there are people defending it means absolutely nothing in the world of video games    they love abuse
what people have to learn
never believe trailers 
never preoder anything

top_comments:
extra tip carry 6 planks with you always you can 1 craft a chest anywhere to repair all your tools including the grappler which makes it actually useful or 2 craft a bed once you get to the right town level which as already stated is good for respawns alternatively you can craft a bed with 10 wood early game and carry both with you
hiya guys if my voice sounds a lil different it is because i have a really bad cold

regarding tip 12 with the grappler
thank you everyone for the comments i wasnt aware the chest tip worked with recharging the grappler so go ahead and craft one now 
it may get patched soon though

really hope you all enjoyed this video and remember to use code rugg in the item shop
thank you all so much for the support 
more lego fortnite videos will be coming later this week
major tips read this
something to keep in mind if you put the grappler in a chest when it has 1 use left and then break the chest it resets the grappler back to 10 uses it makes the grappler very work getting

another tip if you take the barrels of tnt found near old broken down buildings  and throw them into clusters of trees or cactuses then it is a quick way to farm the dessert snd frost biome logs
crazy how far people went with knowledge of this mode while im only at 3rd village lvl great video as always
for heavy wool have your villagers assigned to create textiles you will get it quite often
if you keep a hearty charm on it can negate low temp or high temp damage you remain at full hp you get the temp hearts so long as your at the first layer of hotcold the amount of damage and how fast it happens will be negated by the charm replacing the temp hearts
i also found out an exploit to reset grappler charges back to 10 it usually happens after i die with it in my inventory and after i pick up my backpack it has 10 shots remaining even when it has been used i also believe it resets after i quit the game and join back and all the charges return edit just tried the durability reset on my purple tools and all of my items got stuck into the ground and i cant pick them up
suggestion i explored my map a bit with nothing on me whenever i came across something interesting i would pick up small stones nearby make a marker and place it there that way i could mark important locations for later exploration and open up the maps view without losing anything then whenever im ready id gear up and already have points of interest marked on my map that i can immediately go to
great tip with the grappler you dont have to break the chest put it in and take it out unfortunately not the same for tools
as of now when it comes to dying of starvation heat or cold there is a way to negate all of them with one item it allowed me to stay in the desert caves infinitely even though i took fire damage the entire time there is an uncommon charm that gives you two additional hearts if youre already full health and it regenerates itself very quickly meaning even if you take instances of damage from starvation heat or cold itll regenerate it self this allowed me to much more quickly and effectively progress through the game especially in regards to those desert caves
more tips 1 instead of crafting chests to refresh your tools just craft a traditional counter under counters as it only costs 8 wood 

2 the grapplers uses can be refreshed just like your tools except its even easier you dont even need to break whatever chestcounter youve built just throw it in a storage thing take it out and its refreshed
thanks for the great tips

my tip is for people starting a new server in survival set up a different server with the same seed in sandbox mode so you can fly around and explore the map faster before setting up your town
i actually would suggest making a grappler it got me out of a really sticky situation in the fire cave and just like your weapon and tools you can reset the durability with the chest exploit 751
i dont know if anyone said this yet but you dont actually need cool headed charms for the desert if you just use a hearty totem you can ignore the damage taken from the hot debuff since the totem will regenerate itself as long as you dont lose your temporary hearts and if you do lose them just eat something and wait a sec to let them regenerate back
you can find sand shells at the beachtropical coast areas access to the cool headed charm is easier due to the creature being found at both locations
craft the grappler it only sucks because it has 10 uses but if you do the chest durability glitch it works on the grappler aswell the grappler is op in the snow biome especially as theres so many steep cliff faces and the grappler makes it so easy to traverse make sure to carry 6 wood planks on you though as you will need to regularly reset it
2 if ur early game run into the snow biome during daytime its warmer then so u wont freeze to death as quickly
also holding a torch in ur offhand will bypass the slow effect
heavy wool thread can also be obtained by your villagers assign them to threading if your on lvl 10 town hall theres a high chance they will give you heavy wool threads or normals
i would say its for sure worth making the grappler just for sticky situations in caves and for traversing the land you can do the durability glitch w the grappler in the chest so just throw it in there when youre fixing your weapons and boom back to 10
fun fact you can reset the uses on the grappler if you put it into a chest and take it out  aim at the highest point of a tree and itll work perfectly with the glider

description:
tom sandoval ariana madix james kennedy scheana shay lala kent and the rest of the cast gear up for season 11 of vanderpump rules watch the season premiere of vanderpump rules january 30th at 87c on bravo

about vanderpump rules
as a mentor and confidant to the group lisa is working to restore some peace between two feuding exes as she attempts to provide perspective lisa is refocusing her expertise on opening a new restaurant in lake tahoe and continuing her success with additional ventures in las vegas   

arianas life was turned upside down after a devastating breakup but shes determined to make the best of a difficult situation although she still shares a home with her ex ariana is moving on and dating a new longdistance boyfriend while working to open the doors to her and katies sandwich shop something about her ariana is embracing the countless opportunities that have come her way
  
recently proclaimed 1 guy in the group james friendships within the circle are stronger than ever and his dj career is booming he bought a house in the valley and is settling into suburban life with his girlfriend ally lewber along with their cat and a dog from james past
  
with more distance from her divorce katie is exploring life as a single woman and dating even if her pursuits strike too close to home for her exhusband tom a previous indiscretion comes to light and threatens to upend her and scheanas renewed friendship as well as her cordial postdivorce relationship with tom
  
lala is still in the midst of a challenging custody battle but being the best mom to ocean remains her priority lala explores fertility treatments and looks for a sperm donor as a single mother she finds an unlikely connection with tom schwartz forming a friendship that neither saw coming but creating tension between her and the rest of the girls as her forgiveness for the toms grows
  
celebrating their oneyear wedding anniversary scheana and husband brock are struggling to connect as they leave the honeymoon stage and settle into their life with a toddler scheana works on new music as a way to express herself she finds herself straddling the lines in the sand within the group as she navigates her relationships with her longtime friends and feuding exes ariana and tom
  
in the aftermath of a scandal that changed his romantic relationships dynamics within the group and the success of his businesses sandoval is working on bettering himself in a fragile state he focuses on repairing the foundations of his friendships when he isnt on the road touring with his band tom sandoval and the most extras he and ariana live under the same roof  locked in a stalemate for the house
  
tom is mending a challenged friendship after taking the heat for his part in his best friends shocking deception embracing a new identity tom bleaches his hair evades exclusivity with a friendpotentiallyturnedgirlfriend and winds up in a surprising love triangle with a new flame and his exwife

video_title: giant minecraft machines are embarrassingly simple
tags: ideas,creative,build,survival,tutorial,How to,MumboJumbo,ThatMumboJumbo,Minecraft,Building,Mumbo,Redstone,Technical,Piston,1.9,1.8,1.10,1.11,Gaming,Game,spotlight,showcase,challenge,command,mini-game,gameplay,playthrough,Let's Play,No Swearing,Family Friendly,mc,mcpe,vanilla,Xbox,360,PS4,PE,pocket edition,mobile
description:
im a fraud in this minecraft redstone video we take a look at how to build giant minecraft flying machines minecraft slimeblock flying machines have been a hobby of mine for years and now im doing a minecraft tutorial on how to build minecraft flying machines from simple minecraft flying machines to adding complexities to creating walking minecraft machines this covers how to build a walking house in minecraft walking minecraft robots and more

filming channel httpswwwyoutubecomuserthatmumbojumbo2
instagram httpswwwinstagramcomofficialmumbo
twitter httpstwittercomthatmumbojumbo
top_comments:

mumbo you should make a machine that retracts fence posts
just in case youre being chased down by a warden 
i like mumbos concept of a basic loop and a jumbled loop however instead of jumbled loop i think it should be called a jumbo loop
if it is soo simple get grian and scar to watch this video and watch them making flying machines
it is kinda funny to see how closely mumbos three design rules parallel the design principles im learning as an engineering undergrad

that way youd have access to tick freeze and tick step which would make these explanations even better imo

incredibly informative grian and scar can now fix docs giant tunnelbore just in time for the end of the season 
i think this makes the whole process so much cooler even if in total its fairly simple
really cool to see the inner workings of how these seemingly complicated machines actually work

top_comments:
i worked for cadillac as a district service manager when that car was introduced in prerelease service meetings it was wellknown from the very beginning that the 864 was planned to be a oneyearonly engine the big problem was the early delco electronics the map sensor was calibrated with tooclose tolerances if the engine hicupped backfired it would shut down there was no repair except to replace the map sensor the bigger problem was replacement stock was the exact same part and it took gm a while before an updated unit could be supplied dealers would disconnect the 864 feature running it as an 8cyl only the press had a field day i inspected a limo in west palm beach florida that the owner wanted all the interior chrome replaced someone had discharged a tear gas device inside the car that caused the damage  the interior chrome pieces came from different suppliers so it was impossible for all of it to be defective and i denied the claim it turned out the limo was owned by the owner of the newspaper the national inquirer famous for stories like i got pregnant by an alien etc they went on a huge hate campaign smearing the vehicle which only threw fuel on the fire those were tough times to be a cadillac district service manager
as a 35 year mechanic i want to say that i admire derek for messing with that aggravating thing respect
the brake drum has traveled farther than the vehicle itself man that was classic
god i love me an old school caddy
the cadillac of despair what a test of wits and perseverance i felt for you through all of it while still bursting into laughter a number of times what an extraordinary episode thanks derek for actually putting this one out 
oh man that brake drum divorcing itself from the vehicle was epic it totally went with the whole project my experience with tbi dumping fuel was the coolant temp sensor 2 wire funny enough the computer relied on coolant temp for fuel mapping could be bad injectors maybe great video laughed a lot
this revival will be a top favorite now just for the amount of genuine laughs as things kept progressively happening the brake drum and the flame out of the  tbi  youre the best man thank you for what you do
what a fight i think this is a great candidate for a junkyard ls or a good old 350
way to keep on fighting through i wouldve thrown in the towel way earlier
i dont think gm tbi fuel injection from the 80s worked like a modern ecu it was a while ago but i think they start in open loop mode with a fixed map on temperature manifold pressure and throttle position once it warms up it switches to closed loop mode where it mostly uses the o2 sensor i bet when it was running good it was because it was in closed loop mode getting it to run long enough to switch to closed loop looked difficult though
id love to see round 2 there are several struggles you had that ive learned from
appreciate the perseverance i would really like to see this thing run and drive even if it means a carb swap or something else along those lines i just dont think this should be how it ends with this rig
man you really worked for every bit of that one

thanks for everything you do
awesome as usual very interesting how the critters migrated the under hood insulation to the exhaust system
even though she didnt drive home this was still a fantastic episode the patience perseverance and diagnostic progression you show is truly impressive shout out to oreilly for the support absolutely loved the brake drums desire to get back on the road
we loved this episode my wife cracked up when the brake drum shot across the shop you cant let this thing beat you toss a modern efi system on it and make it a super nice take momma out to dinner rig
i definitely want to see a carburetor swap and a general engine bay cleanup where you get rid of as many hoses and wires as possible
this has to be one of my favorite episodesthe runaway brake drum fleeing the scene and then the fire in the holeabsolutely hilarious  i laughed so hard my dogs starting barking at me
hell of an effort i dont think ive seen you slither the floor that much ever the launch of the drum was classic my brotherinlaw and some other students at an agriculture engineering school in mo began the design on this engine in the 70s for an ag engine not a passenger car the story goes that the college sold the idea to gm and they took it and proceeded to wreck it

for anyone wondering there are two types of birds nesting and nonnesting a nesting birds babies are called nestlings and when first hatched are super fragile needs constant food cannot walk or fly is completely featherless and takes longer to mature a nonnesting birds babies are just called chicks and when first hatched can walk dont need constant food cannot fly and has a fuzzy coat that keeps them warm independantly of their mother

chickens turkeys quail pheasants ducks geese etc all give birth to chicks which is why you may be thinking that baby birds are easy to care for they kinda just figure out life on their own nestling birds need special equipment foods and sometimes medicines to be raised by humans you need to feed them every 46 hours with a syringe keep them warm and keep them hydrated which is harder to do when they are kept warm for the duration of their infancy you basically have to nap instead of sleep or have a second person assist you as you both plan your sleep schedules to do a 1212 shift you need to take care of them for something or rather every 3 hours on the hour raising a bird seems really cool but dont raise a nestling unless you know everything about the species you are trying to raise

video_title: hunting for water  gold to revive my abandoned ghost town
tags: Cerro Gordo,Ghost Town,Gold Prospecting,Water Exploration,Abandoned Places,Historic Mines,Treasure Hunt,Ghost Town Life,Cerro Gordo Adventures,Cerro Gordo Exploration,Ghost Town Series,Urban Exploration,Mining History,Cerro Gordo Projects,Cerro Gordo Update,Abandoned Towns,Cerro Gordo Progress,Water Witches,Water Dowsing
description:
hello there this past month was a great one up here at cerro gordo we had a lot of experts come to look for things like water gold and wood we made progress on a lot of projects and even started some new ones 

thank you all so so much for all the support over the years it means the world to me

check out jason at mbmmllc and dan at danhurd 

also  i wrote a book i have been working on this for almost two years now and i am so excited to finally announce it i put my put my heart and soul into this thing and really dug deep on making sense of these past 3 years living up here the book has all sorts of new stories insights and history of the town i think its the best content ive ever made

if youve ever got anything out of this channel i hope youll consider preordering the book it is a huge way to show support for everything going on and would mean the world to me 

amazon httpswwwamazoncomgpproduct0593578449
barnes  noble signed copies httpsbitly3qrzoyb
booksamillion httpsbitly3tnauks
bookshoporg httpsbitly3rzb5bn

available in all formats  hardcover ebook and audio httpswwwpenguinrandomhousecombooks709605ghosttownlivingbybrentunderwood

if you do preorder the book before jan 1 2024 i have some special bonuses for you 

 buy 1 book and get unreleased pages from the book and an unreleased full video of some of the best mine exploration ive never shown 
 buy 5 books and ill send you a signed page from the draft manuscript for you to have 
 buy 10 books and youll get an invite to a vip party  tour of cerro gordo hosted by me at cerro gordo in april of 2024 
 forward all receipts of the book to bookcerrogordominescom 

for more behind the scenes photos check out my instagram httpswwwinstagramcombrentwunderwood

merch cerro gordo tshirts and more httpsstorecerrogordominescom 

mailing address po box 490 lone pine ca 93545

top_comments:
i worked at chuck e cheese as a manager for 2 years and it was a daily question where is the animatronics is it true kids got stuffed in them do you know fnaf
for those wondering scott said he wouldnt make fnaf a real thing as a park restaurant or anything like that because hes scared someone would make the games real to become famous or something
you know fnaf has messed you up when matpat tells the story of a real guy and you treat it like a lore theory
i think the main mistake a lot of family friendly companies are making is that they put way too much focus on being unoffensive to the parents theyre so careful not to give the parents any reason to not bring their kids to their restaurants that they completely neglect to give the kids any reason to want to go in the first place would a fnaf event at chuck e cheese upset some parents sure but kids would be begging to go check it out and that would drum up so much more business than theyd potentially lose
remember that chuck e cheese was the actual main reason why fnaf happened in the first place so i think the best thing charles entertainment could do is not only collaborate chuck e cheese with fnaf but also possibly make a trip down memory lane to fnafs history and most chuck e cheeses history as well
as a kid in the 90s the chuck e cheese animatronics were barely working and they were scary to me timeskip to now and as someone who loves fnaf i would love to see a collab between fnaf and chuck e cheese heck im sure the kids going to chuck e cheese love fnaf
as someone who works at a main event as a technician i can attest to the fact that maintanence and repair of attractions takes a lot of money especially depending on what broke if its a lane generally the parts are gonna be expensive due to the wear and tear they need to endure and how big they are and with how pricey bowling is they get paid for on that alone as bowling next to dining and scheduled events are the big money makers games on the other hand have to pay for themselves due to their high initial cost and make their revenue based on who plays them throughout the day via game cards or tokens if a part on a game breaks down the cost of the part comes from how much it makes so if a coin pusher breaks a motor and the motor is 130 and the game makes 1000 a week than its an easy buy if a shooter game has its gun break down and the gun is 900 but the game makes 500 a week its a lot harder to justify keeping the game especially if its an old one another example would be if te game promotes a gimmick that contributes nothing to gameplay and is purely funcosmetic if thst breaks down and te revenue the game brings in isnt enough to justify fixing the gimmick but the game works regardless than it can be left operable just without that flashing light more so if the gimmick continuously breaks i imagine with big animatronic characters this kind of logistics is applied even more so as they are an attraction but dont necessarily bring in their own revenue theyre just for show like a tv and rely on what the resturant earns to keep their upkeep in check
the fact matpat still remembers fnacfive nights at candy and mentions it is amazing
its actually interesting that chuck e cheese was starting to file for bankruptcy similar to how fnaf kind of did it mostly in the first game this possibly states that chuck e cheese is now officially fnaf but in real time
i think the problem they want to avoid is if they lean too heavily into the fnaf side then some psycho might attempt to recreate the games irl thats exactly why scott has said he doesnt want really pizzerias
i think instead of a partnership with fnaf cc should invent their own game with their own lore and a fresh backstory
no matter the reason i think its really sad that theyre retiring the animatronics chuck e cheese was such a big part of my childhood and it wont be the same without them even though i thought the animatronics were creepy back then
lets be honest fnaf didnt make animatronics creepy it just brought that sentiment to the forefront
as a chuck e cheese fan this episode title sure did make me curious on how this topic would be covered lol
tbh i think a large portion of factors can be mentioned in regards to the animatronic band removal but its still pretty tragic 
they used to have a slogan that said make magic without it were just another pizza place and now that feels bitter because of them removing the one thing that really set them apart from anything else 
its honestly quite a shame and as nice as it is that theyre keeping the band at northridge that band has several issues that i doubt theyll fix anytime soon
i hope more stores keep their band or more reopen with the band as a retro store gimmick however its all unpredictable at this point tbh wouldnt surprise me if the brand itself dies within the next decade
some chuck e cheese locations used to have interactive consoles where kids could look at different camera feeds placed around the restaurant they should have kept those around to appeal to fnaf fans
i would definitely prefer that we keep some tactile stuff like these animatronics around theres just simply no comparing a screen and a physical robot the latter is way more fun but uh i dont think fully going in on horror is the move here
im amazed at how much business sense matpat shows on food theory
i remember going to chuck e cheese with my uncle as a kid he worked with all sorts of technology so we always stayed after the place closed while he talked to the staff about the robots lights and sound system i remember being right there on the stage and looking at the animatronics up close and even being able to look at the ways they hid some of the animatronics that werent working without removing them from the stage altogether 

it is one of my favorite memories and i am truly saddened by the fact that they are getting rid of the animatronics
imo if they did make a fnafstyle eatertainment experience id imagine itd be a lot like the movie the animatronics are actually guys in muppet suits and during peak dining hours they close up the stage for supposed maintenance only for the stage to open up a few minutes later and reveal that one of the actors is just inexplicably gone

about demon slayer kimetsu no yaiba
demon slayer kimetsu no yaiba is based on the manga series by koyoharu gotoge published under shueishas jump comics which consists of 23 volumes and over 150 million copies in publication the animation production is by ufotable

the story begins when tanjiro kamado a boy whose family is killed by a demon joins the demon slayer corps to turn his younger sister nezuko back into a human after she is transformed into a demon in april 2019 the tv anime series demon slayer kimetsu no yaiba first premiered with the tanjiro kamado unwavering resolve arc followed by the release of the feature film mugen train in october 2020 and the tv series mugen train arc and entertainment district arc from october 2021 and the swordsmith village arc from april 2023 in spring 2024 the new longawaited tv series hashira training arc will premiere

description:

free ways to support our productions
httpbitlyjoingwtw



were jason and nikki wynn  a couple of modernday documentarians perpetual travelers and seekers of tall tales  

weve been chasing our curiosity around the world on wheels and keels since 2011 why  because curiosity is the key to unlocking life  it pushes us outside our comfort zone softens our assumptions and helps us embrace the great unknown  the more we let our curiosity lead the way the more we discover about ourselves and the world around us

our home is also our transportation and we spend weeks away from civilization and sometimes land  selfreliance and living a sustainable lifestyle are a must  its all about managing our resources and were always looking for new and better ways to do so  

weve lived off the grid for over 10 years now in everything from a van to rv to a sailboat and over time we have learned a lot about renewable energy creating safe drinking water and managing our waste

our journey is everevolving but the mission remains the same cultivatecuriosity

timestamps if you like to jump around

when the npcs are glitching out like that then try talking to them first  if that doesnt work then continue doing what youre doing
one thing i like about the prefab builds is theyre modular you can knock out the walls on a double shack and replace them with shack doors to create passible outbuildings
biggest building issue ive had is there doesnt seem to be a way to change the elevation of your nonprefab foundations making it hard to keep things at the same level
destroying bushes is actually easier with a sword
for me rn traveling is the main issue it cant be that u have to walk 10 mins just to get to a cave once u mined the 2 caves kinda nearby your village or walk 20 mins to the next dessert just so you can die bcs u didnt know that the mobs there are way stronger
you can also build campfires inside of caves instead of using torches  yes it costs more wood however itll light up the cave for you so its easier to find whatever your looking for
before commenting understand that deliberately exploiting is cheating not a tip
dont just throw away tools that you dont use use a villager as a follower and you can give them those tools and they will use it they can hold multiple tools and just swap to the best one depending on the situation
really fantastic synopsis and tips you nailed it i would add 
build your first village at the edge of a desert border and near a knotwood cave not where you spawn into the game make your life easier and everything more efficient
build a bed at the mouth of a cave as a save point if you die you respawn in your bed you wont have to travel back to your quest point
empty almost all of your backpack before beginning a quest youll need the inventory slots
pack for a trip max wood planks to build repair chests cooked food snowberry shakes or cheesy burgers
its good to stack lumber mills it makes crafting so much quicker
something i always do with the spare pickaxes is give it to one designated adventuring villager and whenever i need to collect granite i take that villager and start going at some rocks unfortunately they still use the pickaxes for fighting even over axes even tho the brown pickaxe does less damage per second compared to just punching so keep that in mind if ur messing about in the dark with them
if you find a boulder on a hill and you need mats just push the boulder down hill towards whatever you need and itll destroy everything for you
go on top of moutains that have large trees cut them down roll the log down to farm granite and wood super easy
i love to make a village stylish and neat it is the most important thing 
man this was one of the coolest surprises of the year  ive always thought a minecraft style game in the lego world would be awesome  whod have thought it would be fortnite to do it
youre lucky  the desert is a 10 minute run away from my spawn point and thats with infinite stamina  however the cold biome is 2 steps away
make glider  build staircases 11 high make platform and u now got a jump pad that will take u way further then the geysers and as soon as i land i build another one so i can basically do the whole map under 10 mins instead of an hour lol i even put a marker on every staircase jump pad so i know the direction they follow back to back  helps tons on the map
stamina bar is important when youre flying with a glider it consumes your stamina while up in the air by the time you run out you will drop from fall damage and die
i personally think temp dont matter as muchbut stam will literally make you op in the beginning bc u can just outrun most early in things like wolves

top_comments:
ive never seen someone buy so many items at a japanese electronic store you must have broken a record 
thanks for having me along for the day man was a lot of fun
hope youve got some snacks ready  this is the longest video weve ever made  which countrys tech do you want us to test next
looks like you guys had an amazing tech shopping spree in japan next time round how about scoping out some everyday gizmos would love to see how japans hometech game stacks up against ours
your one of my favorite youtubers arun you always have a fresh happy smile on your face
fun fact there was actually another company in japan called logitec its spelled the same as logitech in japanese and they were in japan before logitech was able to open up anything in japan so they had to change their name to logicool in japan only to avoid a name conflict
this is so surreal ive been letting the abroad in japan channel build up videos to binge and after the frozen frontier series i went back to another video from arun to finish it and i was like oh yeah theres a new video i wanna watch that and now seeing chris walk in was like

the only way i can express the feeling was imagine you watch a tv show and then switch to another tv show only to see the character from the other tv show nonchalantly walk in like what
that trackball mouse is something i used at my job back in the late 80s early 90s youve never seen one before 
this was a great collab  love to watch both yours and chriss channels 
that store completely blows my mind i could be in there for days
love the longer video btw this was enjoyable to watch
i might be one of the few japanese subscribers of your channel your videos are awesome and i genuinely hope more people here can enjoy them maybe difficult because of the language barrier tho hope youll come back soon
i think i can go an entire day exploring this shop without rest or food genuinely amazing
the timing of those memes is just chefs kiss
i love how excited arun gets about this stuff that has been available all over the world for years now lol
the ball mouse is called a trackball pretty useful especially helping reduce rsi its been available for years in the west but we hardly made a fuss about it also for fine control you can use a hotkey on your keyboard to move super slow to be accurate
3920 first time in japan over twenty years ago taught me that rice is not a bulk up  filler  meal item but  something to be enjoyed as much as any other item on the plate even in something as texturally and flavour diverse as a shojin ryori meal the rice is as much a part of the experience and been mildly evangelical about spreading that opinion  its a hard sell to a lot of westerners   
but  its my occasional once or twice a year life mission
im a japanese in the uk and i really enjoyed this  shame the kids watch wont work in the uk with child safety more of an issue here than in japan it would probably do relatively well here  i love rice cookers and bought all my friends one over a couple of years  yum asia do good ones in the uk and not as expensive as the japanese leader but similar technology i didnt see it in the video and i know its not a cooking channel but i hope you washed the rice first 
its my dream to go to japan definitely visiting this tech place when i eventually go 
touch ball mice are used a lot in north america canada more then usa they are used a lot for work in fields that use programs such as autocad maya blender and image creation such as krita photoshop etc they work very well for a lot of things even gaming i loved mine but the ball has a small accident exactly like the one you had when you picked it up my sister and i nicked named the ball  booots its a joke from baldurs gate 2 with the gigantic minatare space hamster and when it would fall out of the rest of the mouse it was one of those moments of almost yelling no boots as if fell and if it hits something hard or even a pointy pebble and gets a scratch on its all over its done and now you are sad i would buy another one should they drop in price as they became more rare in stores and the reason that is important is unlike a mouse that you can usually find a way to hold relatively weird mice with ball mice you need to make sure it fits your hand in a very comfortable way while you control the ball with your thumb so it makes sure you can do that for extended amount of time so if it does not fit your hand right you will hate it with a passion when it fits right you wonder why you have not been using this type of mouse for your whole life so you need to make sure its the right fit for you and make sure you never drop the ball as that is how boots died one little scratch and the dream was dead but got i believe 4 years out of her before that unfortunate accident after that time no stores were carrying them except one and it was a crap one and a very shitty size and quality 
final thing there are some that use 24 optical sensors that make it be able to do much more control in a 3d environment such as 123d autocad and others but it also makes games such as mmorpgs fps and rts a joy to play and target with insane accuracy for headshots especially the multiple sensor ones

so find the right one that fits your hand and has the amount of sensors you want with the dpi you want and never look back that said you should still have a normal mouse as sometimes if your hand is tired or your thumb is soar or something like that a normal mouse can be a little easier to use for those moments
i love coverage like this id love it even more if you got a little input from the target audience of each device for example the portable record players were old tech in the late 80s a portable record player was one of my first repairs id be surprised if those devices have had any innovation since then i suspect that the target audience for those is not tech enthusiasts or vinyl enthusiasts but instead retirees whose entire music collection is in vinyl and are just happy to still be able to play what they have

i felt this way about a few of the items in this video and some recent videos i think its especially important to get input when visiting other cultures and passing judgement on their choices

other than that youve done an amazing job as always and i cant wait to see the next one
thank you so much for giving us so much quality content and being so interesting you look like you had a fun time
this is a dream collab for a long time i watched you guys channels and appreciated you in every video but seeing you conquer the biggest electronic store together is such a nice surprise japan lifestyle carries both futuristic prospects and the relics of the past so any kind of video from there is bound to be the most interesting tech and lifestyle content
arun consistently amazes me with the incredible dedication and effort he puts into his videos his passion for technology shines through in every frame and its truly commendable the buying and reviewing tech series is without a doubt the best out there  his thorough insights engaging delivery and genuine excitement for the latest gadgets make each video an absolute delight to watch keep up the fantastic work arun your hard work does not go unnoticed and your content continues to be a beacon for tech enthusiasts like myself

woooeee folks let me tell ya i did not intend for this to be such a huge project but when nick and i pulled up to the marketplace sellers driveway and realized this dollhouse was 5 literal feet tall i knew i was in for a doozy but who would i be if i let that stop me so here we go 
ive been seeing a lot of people online turning dollhouses into gingerbread houses and i wanted a piece of that whimsical action i felt like this frozen arendelle dollhouse would be perfect for a little victorian twist so i grabbed my spray paint fake icing and pure determination to make this giant lady a snack
please enjoy heheheeh

top_comments:
new bad coffee trend drink only positively charged coffee grounds throw away the identical negative charged grounds
i am absolutely certain that if 1 of humanity increased the level of interest and passion in what they did regardless of what that may be to even a fraction of what you do with and for coffee the world would be a much better place
thank you james for encouraging people through coffee to do more do better and question what they do
the reason youre not seeing particle size differences in your particle sized analyser is probably because it breaks up the electroclumps during the measuring process no idea the details of how the machine works but it would be far from surprising if it was violent enough to the micron sized particles to break up the electroclumps into their constituent grains
its fascinating that the spritzing makes a measurable difference to the extraction of the espresso i could totally see well in theory this should have a marginal benefit but in reality itll probably never mean anything but its amazing that they were able to actually measure a meaningful quantitative change
i love the citizen science your channel is promoting and that youre encouraging mixed and unclear results to be shared there is a signal here we just cant see it yet keep sharing keep signal boosting and keep experimenting
if you close your eyes you can experience what its like to have jon hamm describe coffee physics to you
i think when collecting data from lots of people tracking relative humidity in the air might be really important i keep my house really dry 30 for 3d printing and i see a massive amount of static cling on my grinder which doesnt have any bottleneck so rh may be a significant source of noise
im not sure why the links arent showing for some people here they are

the google survey 
httpsformsgleaggetuddcnquvrzr7
the paper direct link httpsbitlywetbeans
supplemental paper httpsbitlycoffeestatic
its always a pleasure to watch these videos and even more of a pleasure to watch james slowly transition from barista to a coffee research scientist with his own laboratory
decided to try this again after giving up on misting beans ages ago  somehow forgot that id since repurposed the atomizer for adding orange blossom water to homemade orgeat  while i cant endorse deliberately using orange blossom water in your coffee grinder it certainly made for an interesting espresso and a real proustian moment while i played what the hell is that weird perfume flavor
my suggestion for the slowing flow rate would be that the coating of water on all the coffee particles drastically increases the capillary action of the coffee bed which usually i would think is fairly hydrophobic if dry the oils in the coffee also probably dont help with that if you try to water dry soil versus slightly damp soil you see the effect of a thin water coating makes orders of magnitude of difference so a stronger capillary force from the already present water allows the coffee to be drawn into the packed bed more evenly and reduces the chances of channels forming leading to higher leaching rates and slower flow rates this is not contrary to what the prof said it might be a combination of both
even though im not that into coffee and usually just guess each time i make it i absolutely love your videos its not just the information but the candor the dedication without obsession and the curiosity i wish there were clones of you making youtube videos on different topics  itd be a better world
this is fascinating  theres a nugget here about grinding frozen coffee  ive been freezing beans for freshness since i use coffee pretty slowly  an unintended result is that when i take out a dose of 18 grams of beans to grind pretty quickly they get covered in a nice even layer of condensation because they are so cold  its like getting a mist and mix for no effort  hard to control the amount which is a function of time and the relative humidity in the room but interesting nonetheless  ive also had no issues with grinding frozen beans in my breville barista express or my fellow ode gen 1 and not surprisingly ive had much less issue with static compared to grinding room temperature beans in the same grinders
man this video is surreal i dont think i ever had a chance to meet him specifically but i was just at a small conference with chris hendon a few months ago and met several of his students and heard a bit about his coffee research i dont think ive ever seen someone ive encountered so closely in such a popular piece of media as this i suspected that he or his work about coffee though he also studies wine and other compounds more relevant to industrial chemistry would show up here eventually though super exciting stuff
i am super excited that you got a particle size analyzer and from a legit analytical science company like anton paar that is an incredible leap towards quantifying the impact of different grinders burrs grind rpm etc which so far has been limited to assumptions wow that instrument is a significant investment too and im thrilled you got to a place where your fame and fortune so to speak can be put towards advanced coffee science to benefit all weird coffee people everywhere

im assuming well be seeing a lot of grinder studies now using that instrument cant wait

james i would love if you could get a multimeter and measure the resistance of the various materials the griders are constructed from particularly where the machines directly contact the ground coffee at the end of the grind my theory is that more conductive surfaces like metals will better dissipate the charges than plastic insulators i think this likely accounts for that initial difference you noticed between different grinders  the eureka mignon oro has a metal spout and cup
i just tried spritzing for pour over coffee there was less static cling which was nice i also noticed that the water drained through the coffee grounds a bit slower i only did it once so it could be a fluke
well done chris and his fellow authors as well as you james what shocks me is that there isnt more science on how to improve the taste of coffee probably because the perception of taste is subjectively measured rather than objectively but there seems to be so much scope to improve brewing and roasting techniques
just a simple thank you james for all you do endlessly fascinating to me and rewarding every time i make my coffee

video_title: the casting of frank stone  reveal trailer
tags: dead by daylight,dbd,behaviour interactive,bhvr,slasher game,survival horror,the casting of frank stone,supermassive games,tcofs,frank stone
description:
wishlist now httpsdbdgame3slyvdo 

the storytelling prowess of supermassive games meets the dead by daylight universe in a haunting horror game that wont soon be forgotten

the shadow of frank stone looms over cedar hills a town forever altered by his violent past as a group of young friends are about to discover stones bloodsoaked legacy cuts deep leaving scars across families generations and the very fabric of reality itself  

in the depths of an oregon steel mill the gruesome crimes of a sadistic killer spawn horrors beyond comprehension delve into the mystery of cedar hills alongside an original cast of characters bound together on a twisted journey where nothing is quite as it seems  

every decision you make shapes the story and impacts the fate of the characters within it brimming with emotional gutpunches and highstakes horror discover how a simple decision can become a truly heartwrenching dilemma

for those who find comfort in the unknown and glee in the grotesque supermassive games cinematic storytelling brings new levels of emotion immersion and intensity to this darkly rich universe

experience a neverbeforeseen look at the wider world of dead by daylight behaviour interactives acclaimed multiplayer horror game filled with spinechilling twists this dark original tale is certain to haunt you long after its over

coming 2024

follow the casting of frank stone
httpswwwinstagramcomcastingfrankstone 
httpstwittercomtcofrankstone

tcofs dbd
top_comments:
for people who are confused

this is a brand new single player game set in the dbd universe featuring as far as we know original characters who will likely come to dbd as skins or characters in the future this is made in collaboration with supermassive games who are known to be behind until dawn the quarry and the dark pictures anthology this game will likely be in a style where the player makes choices that will alter the story it will release sometime in 2024

by the way the song is daylight by david kushner
this game has gone so far its insane
it actually looks so good more dead by daylight lore i cant wait
this could be supermassives best game since until dawn well done to both companies im excited  
i love how his helmet is shaped like entitys jaws solid way to reveal more about the character through his design
something about seeing from the world of dead by daylight with solemn music in the background is emotional like for the past 7 years excitement around dead by daylight had always been about what outside thing they brought in like license chapters for the first time hype is generated by someone else announcing that they are collaborating with dead by daylight im also so excited to be able to see dead by daylight in a more cinematic lense finally being able to properly experience the horror of dbd
theres a lot of symbolism in the name the casting of frank stone frank stoke being some form of character casting either being casted by the entity for what we know as the trials or casting in terms of being shaped or molded by the entity as well as casting and stone in the title could imply the saying casting the first stone so this may very well be some form of beginning to the story we know this may have been where the first stone of our story is casted
i like how the killer already looks so unsure about what he wants to do and what hes becoming and when hes shown off in the mask it looks like hes just exhausted and so regretful of whatever deal he made with the entity
you guys have no idea how happy i am to see you two collab together cant wait for this game
if they really want this to feel special i hope we also get to make choices from the killer pov remember that most killers are as much victims of the entity as the survivors and want to escape this purgatory
some hunches i have about this game

1 this could possibly be the first killer that arrived in the entities realm and tells the story about how he got there before being tossed into the void
2 the screams in the background are most likely the four main characters being held captive by said killer who at some point during the game manage to escape and you have to help them make it out alive 
3 the entitys full physical form is seen for the first time that being a gigantic spider while it is said that the realm itself is the entity ex trees birds pallets etc on the official dbd wiki it states that the entities most preferred form is that of a spider resembling something from stephen kings it 
4 its my strong hunch that whoever it is that is supposed to canonically survive the game will most likely show up as a future survivor in the core game 

all in all im really excited for this game cant wait to get my hands on it

edit when i was looking at the steam page for the game i also noticed a pharmaceutical store that had afterpiece tonic on it so well probably get to meet a younger version of the clown at some point or maybe a close relative that refers to him

edit 2 did some thinking and i believe that we will experience the 4 main characters get taken by the entity which will result in them encountering frank stone and we will experience a full trial in a more cinematic perspective this would explain why his workbench is covered in nature by the time the others show up so before that happens its really more so getting to know the towns history and the scars frank left behind
this is an infinitely more interesting collaboration than i thought it was going to be would be super fun to get some outfits or even chapters related to their other games
felt a surprising amount of emotion from this trailer very well made
you can see the reference from the song itself frank doesnt really want to kill but hes being forced by the entity

hiding all of our sins from the daylight  his eyes speaks from the sins he committed such a powerful trailer indeed
im crying seeing how far and how much dead by daylight has grown and i get a shot of nostalgia whenever i play this game
finally expanding the dbd franchise in a way that makes the most sense not everyone likes 4v1s but a lot of people like horror based story games 

imagine new characters or existing characters story fleshed out in an interactive way 

this is a good sign
this has to be one of my favorite trailers you guys have made the music the animation its just great
for anyone wondering what the gameplay and chase sequences will be like

most of the game is cutscenes where you make choices that determine events that happen and who livesdies all action sequences during the game are also cutscenes with things like quick time events for example if you had to jump over a pallet to escape the killer in the game a buttom would appear on the screen if you press the button before it vanishes you jump over the pallet if you dont then the character is either permenantly dead or lives through luck somehow the rest of the gameplay while not being chased will basically be 3rd person and you will just walk around through areas finding clues and trying to escape

also if you want more games like this check out until dawn the quarry and the 4 games in the dark picture anthology
this trailer is a masterpiece this music and this camera optics
perfect music choice i am so in this has to be one of the best directed trailers for anything i have ever seen well done on both companies you guys knocked it out of the park

video_title: 6 dead nearly 2 dozen injured after severe storms tear through central tennessee
tags: tornado,Tennessee
description:
tornado weather 
 severe storms that tore through central tennessee killed six people saturday and sent about two dozen to the hospital as homes and businesses were damaged in multiple cities

three people including a child were killed after an apparent tornado struck montgomery county north of nashville near the kentucky state line county officials said in a news release and the nashville emergency operation center said in a post on a social media account that three people were killed by severe storms there montgomery county officials said another 23 there were treated for injuries at hospitals

video_title: starship  second flight test
description:
on november 18 2023 starship successfully lifted off at 702 am ct from starbase on its second integrated flight test 

while it didnt happen in a lab or on a test stand it was absolutely a test what we did with this second flight will provide invaluable data to continue rapidly developing starship 

the test achieved a number of major milestones helping us improve starships reliability as spacex seeks to make life multiplanetary the team at starbase is already working final preparations on the vehicles slated for use in starships third flight test 

congratulations to the entire spacex team on an exciting second flight test of starship

follow us on xcomspacex for continued updates on starships progress

video_title: lego fortnite gameplay trailer

explore vast open worlds where the magic of lego building and fortnite collide
collect food and resources craft items build shelter and battle enemies solo or team up with up to seven friends

get creative in building and customizing your ultimate home base using lego elements collected from the world around you then recruit villagers to gather materials and help survive the night gear up and drop into deep caves in search of rare resources and hidden areas 

find the ultimate survival crafting lego adventure in fortnite the journey is only just beginning with new world building gameplay features and more lego style outfits arriving in updates starting early 2024

this man has professionalism in 70 of the entirety of video games

this is easily top 3 favourite games of all time such a unique game and every level is a boss apart from run n guns absolutely love it

video_title: hoonigan ken blocks electrikhana two one more playground mexico city in the audi s1 hoonitron
tags: electrikhana,electrickhana,Hoonigan,electric gymkhana,audi hoonitron,hoonigan racing,Ken Block,ken block gymkhana,audi s1 hoonitron,hoonigan ev,audi s1 quattro,car drift,cars,awd,modified cars,donuts,electric car,hooning,electricana,brian scotto,hoonicorn,juca,juca viapri,drifting,paddle shift,kb43,43i,43 institute,burnouts,ev race car,audi electric car,electrichana,mexico city,mexico df,audi etron,audi e tron,audi e-tron,Kb43ver,Кен Блок,jucaviapri
description:
in november of 2022 ken block and the hoonigan team headed to mexico city mx to film the next installment of the electrikhana series with the audi s1 hoonitron just over one month later the devastating loss of ken block meant that the project was shelved  until now

block the hoonigans and audi continue pushing the limits of whats possible in the performance ev world with electrikhana two sliding through iconic areas of mexico city in blocks infamously aggressive rallyinspired driving style improving the car immediately after the first film block and audi built on important development lessons from their experience in las vegas

a big thank you goes out to the partners who helped make electrikhana two possible

the gta 6 release date is 2025 on ps5 and xbox series xs

video_title: handson with gemini interacting with multimodal ai
description:
gemini is our natively multimodal ai model capable of reasoning across text images audio video and code this video highlights some of our favorite interactions with gemini learn more and try the model httpsdeepmindgooglegemini 

explore our prompting approaches here httpsgooglehowitsmadegemini 

for the purposes of this demo latency has been reduced and gemini outputs have been shortened for brevity

subscribe to our channel httpswwwyoutubecomgoogle
tweet with us on twitter httpstwittercomgoogle
follow us on instagram httpswwwinstagramcomgoogle
join us on facebook httpswwwfacebookcomgoogle

019 multimodal dialogue
132 multilinguality
204 game creation
231 visual puzzles
317 making connections
339 image  text generation
406 logic  spatial reasoning
455 translating visuals
527 cultural understanding
top_comments:
absolutely mindblowing the amount of understanding the model exhibits here is way way beyond anything else
im glad to see google back in the game this looks next level
very impressive want to try it
fyi this is embellished a bit its still extremely cool and impressive and i am so excited to see these advances but theres a fair amount they have to do to get to this exact state in a viral video demonstrating geminis capabilities google took significant artistic license it showed a user speaking with gemini but was actually representing a text conversation it showed a moving video but was feeding gemini still images it showed fast responses but sped those up it showed tight model outputs but shortened them for brevity it showed brief prompts eliciting terrific answers but listed longer prompts in a blog post  from big technlology by alex kantrowitz
the realtime element is by far the most impressive these sorts of asynchronous interactions are what ai has been missing thus far
just one problem the video isnt real we created the demo by capturing footage in order to test geminis capabilities on a wide range of challenges then we prompted gemini using still image frames from the footage and prompting via text parmy olsen at bloomberg was the first to report the discrepancy
that is incredibly impressive there were clearly some hidden prompts as it kept understanding switching contexts but still it was highly impressive
im just looking forward to when they hook up this kind of ai into one of those boston dynamics robots and we can finally have robot servants we can talk to like we always dreamed of in scifi it increasingly feels like we are finally living in the future like we expected we would by the year 2000
when this is really working as being shown it is indeed mindblowing great job

its truly fascinating to see what ai is now capable of
this is incredible now if we can combine this with an embodied agent that can navigate through the world plan out sequences of actions from interactions with the user and use rl to learn from mistakes and learn about the user that would be gg
i cant imagine the amount of data used to train gemini this is next level and if it has open ais new voice type then this will be the greatest multimodal ai
its kinda crazy how intelligent this ai is on the fly and is considered a basic model by them the stuff they have behind the scenes is far more advanced
i find this mindblowing although what im more exited about what is going to happen next for the past year openai has been without competition so they have probably not been in full gear now that google and openai have caught on it sure to mean an ai race is going to start with a ridicolous speed of progress
fascinating  i cant wait to see what weve accomplished in another 5 years
this has a lot of potential as an ai workbench for your child to replace their entire education from kindergarten to university

video_title: tesla cybertruck v lamborghini urus drag race
tags: carwow,mat watson,car review,new car review,car review 2023,new car 2023,tesla,tesla cybertruck,cybertruck,cyber truck,tesla cyber truck,cybertruck drag race,cybertruck hp,cybertruck bhp,cybertruck performance,tesla cybertruck drag race,electric suv,electric pick-up,electric pick-up truck,lambo,lamborghini,lamborghini urus,urus,lambo urus,lamborghini urus drag race,lambo urus drag race,urus drag race,cybertruck v urus
description:
welcome to the ultimate petrol vs electric drag race 

weve got our hands on the allnew tesla cybertruck and its lining up alongside the a lamborghini urus but which will come out on top  petrol or electric 

well lets check out the stats starting with the cybertruck it rolls up equipped with three electric motors and they combine to produce 845hp and 930nm of torque the starting price of the dualmotor edition is around 49000 but for this trimotor cyberbeast edition itll cost you around 96000 in terms of weight the cybertruck tips the scales at just over 3 tonnes it also has a top speed of 130mph 

then we have the lambo its packing a 4litre twinturbo v8 under the bonnet and this can produce 650hp and 850nm of torque power is sent to all four wheels via an 8speed torque converter gearbox and its a whole lot lighter than the tesla tipping the scales at 2200kg it also has a much bigger top speed coming in at 190mph 

so the cybertruck has the urus beat when it comes to performance stats but will the extra weight drag it down theres only one way to find out for sure lets race

video_title: kung fu panda 4  official trailer
description:
kung fu panda 4  in theaters march 8

this spring for the first time in almost a decade comedy icon jack black returns to his role as po the worlds most unlikely kung fu master with a hilarious buttkicking new chapter in dreamworks animations beloved actioncomedy franchise kung fu panda 4 

after three deathdefying adventures defeating worldclass villains with his unmatched courage and mad martial arts skills po the dragon warrior golden globe nominee jack black is called upon by destiny to  give it a rest already more specifically hes tapped to become the spiritual leader of the valley of peace

that poses a couple of obvious problems first po knows as much about spiritual leadership as he does about the paleo diet and second he needs to quickly find and train a new dragon warrior before he can assume his new lofty position 

even worse theres been a recent sighting of a wicked powerful sorceress chameleon oscar winner viola davis a tiny lizard who can shapeshift into any creature large or small and chameleon has her greedy beady little eyes on pos staff of wisdom which would give her the power to resummon all the master villains whom po has vanquished to the spirit realm 

so pos going to need some help he finds it kinda in the form of crafty quickwitted thief zhen golden globe winner awkwafina a corsac fox who really gets under pos fur but whose skills will prove invaluable in their quest to protect the valley of peace from chameleons reptilian claws this comedic oddcouple duo will have to work together in the process po will discover that heroes can be found in the most unexpected places 

the film features the voice talent of returning stars academy award winner dustin hoffman as kung fu master shifu james hong everything everywhere all at once as pos adoptive father mr ping academy award nominee bryan cranston as pos birth father li and emmy award nominee ian mcshane as tai lung shifus former student and archnemesis oscar winner ke huy quan everything everywhere all at once joins the ensemble as a new character han the leader of the den of thieves 
 
kung fu panda 4 is directed by mike mitchell dreamworks animations trolls shrek forever after and produced by rebecca huntley dreamworks animations the bad guys the films codirector is stephanie ma stine shera and the princesses of power in 2008 the academy awardnominated 2008 inaugural chapter kung fu panda became dreamworks animations highestgrossing original animated film and launched a franchise that has earned more than 18 billion at the global boxoffice
