video_title: the day before disaster sets a dangerous precedent
tags: the day before,scam,scam game,asset flip,fntastic
description:
the day before launched 4 days ago and proved to be a monumental failure  so much so that the studio shutdown and is likely running with the money

special thanks to bigfrytv for his gameplay
hollyrexs clip httpswwwtwitchtvhollyrexclipbombastichyperalmonditsboshytimeyk9mhvw17bk6cm
top_comments:
steam has taken the game down  you can no longer buy it  apparently steam also holds money for 30 days  theyre also allowing refunds no matter how long you have played  so it looks like the developers jumped ship too early
luckily steam is accepting refunds for players past the 2 hour mark this was too much of a scam even for steam
players and valve should put these guys in court
one thing i have learned over the years is there are people defending it means absolutely nothing in the world of video games    they love abuse
what people have to learn
never believe trailers 
never preoder anything
wait till the game is fully released
this is one of those cases where we need to make it publicly visible who the scammers are that worked on or rather orchastrated this game so people will know if these scumbags decide to just make a new development team and try the same shit again
not to mention fntastic used volunteers in their development process they asked people to help develop their game and in exchange the volunteers received participation certificates and free codes for the game every single stage of development had the stench of shady grifter all over it
the fact that the studio literally said shit happens is wow
level i gotta give some credit to the devs because what they put together isnt that easy
seconds later
also level random guy on reddit is recreating the game by himself  
i remember watching you when i was in middle school and you made airsoft videos im happy to see youre still at it man keep up the hard work 
imagine if they released the source code for the community to use the foundation to make the game it was supposed to be
keep an eye on the ranchers it was announced at tga a year ago and is going down the same route  even after a successful kickstarter
i have a feeling this will not be the last time this happens regardless of whether or not fntastic is actually in the red or not other people will see this as an possiblt opportunity expect to see people learning from the errors made by fntastic and performing scams better keep an eye out everyone do not buy any new game from a new and unknown developer until you see content creators review it and give the all clear be cautious and stay safe and hopefully this trend will die before it takes flight
the frustrating thing about this is that consumers were told in no uncertain terms by practically all the gaming media that this was a scam this was made clear for them for pretty much a year before release yet they bought it anyway its pretty hard to imagine they could have missed all the negative coverage that was out there over that length of time
my biggest issue is i was keeping an eye on this and planned to get it for my self but every video and trailer i watched i kept sitting there feeling like this was a cash grab and dont touch it but the cinematic trailers they did it looked great
i always follow the rule of if it looks and sounds too good to be true it probably is especially when they never show real in game footage
the gaming community should keep an eye on these people apparently they have a secondary studio or already changed their name to eight points i feel theyll continue their scam practices until they are demanded or something in the legal pathway of things
been appreciating your efforts since bf3  thank you for what you do
imagine if 10 legitimate developers like that guy joined on to make that parody i bet they could have a functional game out in about 6 months to a year thats making the game actually playable and improving on things too
i think this is a good thing long term for consumers if this doesnt get people to wise up and quit shelling out money for games without a good idea of what theyre getting something with a lot of thirdparty gameplay videos then theres no hope for video gamers

video_title: 3 simple fixes saved me 10000 on a main dealer quote jaguar xk x150
description:
support nr27 and get
1 members only monthly live chats 2 priority replies to comments 3 loyalty badges
httpswwwyoutubecomchannelucerr8b5sc1owxi31n6wzmiajoin

big thanks to smart rimz for their help with the wheels do look them up if you need anything  httpswwwsmartrimzcom

tayna car batteries are fantastic and supply all my car batteries use the code number27yt for a further 5 off   httpswwwtaynacouk      

and do check out auto reserve for your jaguar spares httpswwwautoreservejaguarcom
top_comments:
the reason jag would have quoted 2600 for the subframe will be mainly labour in this situation you really need to take the subframe out of the car remove all rust down to bare metal and then paintwaxoyl it while its out of the car what youve done is basically put a rust proof layer on top of rust this will stop new moisture getting into the subframes metal but it wont stop the rust you left from spreading underneath the coating so it will look all nice and new but the metal will continue to deteriorate
jack next time you polish headlights i recommend putting masking tape on the paint around the lights first as its easy to accidentally polish through the paint on the edges of the panels  it lets you see if youre going past the edge of the light too often and gives the paint a touch of protection before it starts to burn off
the headlights will need a coat of uv resistant lacquer to last else youll need to polish them again in 1218 months as they will go cloudy again no biggie but worth getting them coated in my personal opinion
personally id have put a neutraliser on the rusty subframe to prevent corrosion coming back under the waxoil  i also always put copper ease on wheel bolts and the hub facing surfaces does make life easier thereafter  looks like its turning into a really usable and still gorgeous car
its great to see you back on the spanners jack as much as i love your reviews this content is what its all about 
i wouldve personally put some rust converter on the subframe as all youve done with the wax oil is lock in the rust which will make it worse long term i see it all the time you need to get rid of the rust first
if you have to attack the lights again please use tape around the surrounding bodywork
great result and just shows how much you can save on dealer quotes however i think the subframe refurb is a bit misleading as youve only really so it would seem got the crap off and sealed the bits you can physically get to you would really need to drop it and take off all the ancillary bits to do it properly just sayin
if you dont already i suggest only using single hex sockets on those kind of wheel nuts double hex ones can damage the this shells and they turn or get stuck in the socket 
found this out the hard way
similarly id avoid using an impact wrench to undo or tighten them as it will break them with no warning use a socket and bar to undo and a torque wrench to tighten
the subframesuspension fix is very temporary
not bad to do and it will buy you some time definitely but i would have removed the thing and either wirewheeled it or better sandblasted it then painted it properly and coating it after that
as a proud canadian owner of an 07 xkr i appreciate your content jack  looking forward to more  thank you
4050 years ago it was common for cars to allow water ingress my old sd1 was always filling up but i find it hard to believe that in this day and age most manufacturers still havent eliminated the problem great video though jack very entertaining  and im so pleased that you saved yourself a small fortune
great channel jack  painting over rust is never a good idea though moisture will get underneath the paint and be trapped which accelerates decay just the lanoguard would be a better idea if you want a quick fix 
the quality of your videos never disappoint jack ive lost count the years ive been watching now
this is what you do best jack i do like the reviews but this is your real strength very entertaining and informative content

major tips read this
something to keep in mind if you put the grappler in a chest when it has 1 use left and then break the chest it resets the grappler back to 10 uses it makes the grappler very work getting

another tip if you take the barrels of tnt found near old broken down buildings  and throw them into clusters of trees or cactuses then it is a quick way to farm the dessert snd frost biome logs
crazy how far people went with knowledge of this mode while im only at 3rd village lvl great video as always
for heavy wool have your villagers assigned to create textiles you will get it quite often
if you keep a hearty charm on it can negate low temp or high temp damage you remain at full hp you get the temp hearts so long as your at the first layer of hotcold the amount of damage and how fast it happens will be negated by the charm replacing the temp hearts
i also found out an exploit to reset grappler charges back to 10 it usually happens after i die with it in my inventory and after i pick up my backpack it has 10 shots remaining even when it has been used i also believe it resets after i quit the game and join back and all the charges return edit just tried the durability reset on my purple tools and all of my items got stuck into the ground and i cant pick them up
suggestion i explored my map a bit with nothing on me whenever i came across something interesting i would pick up small stones nearby make a marker and place it there that way i could mark important locations for later exploration and open up the maps view without losing anything then whenever im ready id gear up and already have points of interest marked on my map that i can immediately go to
great tip with the grappler you dont have to break the chest put it in and take it out unfortunately not the same for tools
as of now when it comes to dying of starvation heat or cold there is a way to negate all of them with one item it allowed me to stay in the desert caves infinitely even though i took fire damage the entire time there is an uncommon charm that gives you two additional hearts if youre already full health and it regenerates itself very quickly meaning even if you take instances of damage from starvation heat or cold itll regenerate it self this allowed me to much more quickly and effectively progress through the game especially in regards to those desert caves
more tips 1 instead of crafting chests to refresh your tools just craft a traditional counter under counters as it only costs 8 wood 

2 the grapplers uses can be refreshed just like your tools except its even easier you dont even need to break whatever chestcounter youve built just throw it in a storage thing take it out and its refreshed
thanks for the great tips

my tip is for people starting a new server in survival set up a different server with the same seed in sandbox mode so you can fly around and explore the map faster before setting up your town
i actually would suggest making a grappler it got me out of a really sticky situation in the fire cave and just like your weapon and tools you can reset the durability with the chest exploit 751
i dont know if anyone said this yet but you dont actually need cool headed charms for the desert if you just use a hearty totem you can ignore the damage taken from the hot debuff since the totem will regenerate itself as long as you dont lose your temporary hearts and if you do lose them just eat something and wait a sec to let them regenerate back
you can find sand shells at the beachtropical coast areas access to the cool headed charm is easier due to the creature being found at both locations
craft the grappler it only sucks because it has 10 uses but if you do the chest durability glitch it works on the grappler aswell the grappler is op in the snow biome especially as theres so many steep cliff faces and the grappler makes it so easy to traverse make sure to carry 6 wood planks on you though as you will need to regularly reset it
2 if ur early game run into the snow biome during daytime its warmer then so u wont freeze to death as quickly
also holding a torch in ur offhand will bypass the slow effect
heavy wool thread can also be obtained by your villagers assign them to threading if your on lvl 10 town hall theres a high chance they will give you heavy wool threads or normals
i would say its for sure worth making the grappler just for sticky situations in caves and for traversing the land you can do the durability glitch w the grappler in the chest so just throw it in there when youre fixing your weapons and boom back to 10
fun fact you can reset the uses on the grappler if you put it into a chest and take it out  aim at the highest point of a tree and itll work perfectly with the glider

video_title: olivia rodrigo tiny desk concert
tags: NPR,NPR Music,National Public Radio,Live,Performance,tiny desk,tiny desk concert,tony desk,tiny concert
description:
hazel cills  december 11 2023
the last time olivia rodrigo performed a tiny desk concert it was two years ago in a deserted dmv office back when pandemic precautions meant artists sadly couldnt play the real desk but this year the singersongwriter returned bringing a handful of songs from her wildly fun sophomore album to the npr music office its much cooler to be here rodrigo says i was saying earlier ive never been starstruck by a room before

many of the songs on guts which earned a special recommendation on npr musics best albums of 2023 list blow out rodrigos sound into colorful grungy poprock fit for a stadium like love is embarrassing performed here with rodrigo on jangly acoustic guitar but the artist builds her set out with guts cuts that fit the intimate setup like the searing vampire her backup vocalists cooing eerily around each of her lines or the potent ode to female jealousy lacy which rodrigo explains started out as a poetry exercise in a college class by the end of her set shes completely alone at the piano for the sobering making the bed and its not difficult to see why shes one of pops most promising rising performers

set list
love is embarrassing
vampire
lacy
making the bed

musicians
olivia rodrigo piano guitar
hayley brownell drums
moa munoz bass
daisy spencer guitar
ashley morgan vocals
elizabeth gaba vocals
julia gartha vocals

tiny desk team
producers suraya mohamed bob boilen
directoreditor joshua bryant
audio engineer josh rogosin
series producer bobby carter 
videographers joshua bryant kara frame elizabeth gillis maia stern
audio assistant valentina rodrguez snchez
production assistant ashley pointer
photographer zayrha rodriguez
tiny desk team hazel cills
vp visuals and music keith jenkins
senior vp programming anya grundmann

nprmusic tinydesk oliviarodrigo
top_comments:
making the bed is so underrated its my fav
tiny desk and snl in the same weekend she is crushing it
her voice is so consistent with her album recordings that alone is so impressive
can we just also appreciate the band and the supporting vocalists they are amazing
set list
0002 love is embarrassing
0415 vampire
0922 lacy
1336 making the bed
lacy and making the bed contain some of olivias most deeply introspective and creatively complexed lyrics on the guts album  lacy vividly defines the internal experience of envy and poetically describes the psychological and emotional tugofwar raging inside of someone that both worships and despises another person who has become an obsession  making the bed defines the internal struggle of accepting the inevitable side effects that come with getting everything that one wants while holding oneself responsible for the decisions that lead to negative results  olivia has said in interviews that she is proud of the songs on guts that explore other topics outside of heartbreak and both of these songs reveal the expanding imagery and specificity of her writing that is both real and relatable especially when performed live
i still have not recovered from the cathartic snl performance and olivia strikes again with four of my favorite songs from guts love the drama and the vocals in each of these songs
want to play your own tiny desk concert unsigned musicians enter the 2024 tiny desk contest between jan 23 and feb 21 learn more httpsnprorgtinydeskcontest
the reason why i like this album so much is because i think it achieves what every artist hopes their followup album will  she is a very mature songwriter and you can hear her mature with her lyrics sour was fun and represented her age very well and i think guts does the samebut she has applied her deeper understanding of herself to her writing and has expressed some of her emotions more vulnerably while still remaining integral to her personal style which initially popularized her even lacy explores the concept of jealously on a much more intricate level than some of the songs on her previous album this is a beautiful second album and such a fluid transition from sour im excited to see what else she puts out in the future
its just incredible how she has a beautiful voice even when she has no auto tune or edits its amazing and an anomaly truly

quick edit ahhh almost 100 likes
 this was far and away one of the best performances by olivia ever finally she sang one of the best songs off guts making the bed which she sang beautifully also lacy was perfect too olivia is so gracious and polite its so refreshing
the energy and joy she puts into love is embarrassing really makes it stand out and come alive relative to the recorded version  shes having fun and it shows  all aree great of course
the personality the talent the kindness we truly made the right artist famous thank you olivia rodrigo 
she is absolutely incredible i love that she took a poetry class and it turned into a song making the bed blew me away
finally us love is embarrassing fans are getting to hear it performed its so good
her tiny desk performances are always so good
i love olivias voice interpretation lyrics and band all of them are just gorgeous at what they do this was one of the best tiny desks ive ever seen she totally deserves her grmmy nominations 
i felt like love is embarrassing was so underrated when it first came out and now she be opening her mini concerts with it im so happy 
this is such a fantastic performance only let down by the mic it is so hard to sing live but she flawlessly sung it
the star power she has proves you dont have to be overly provocative to sell just pure talent

video_title: i stuffed a tenner in my pocket and walked north
tags: tenner,ten pounds,ten pound,geowizard,tenner in my pocket,£10,£10 in my pocket,ten pounds in my pocket,in my pocket,walking north,head north,heading north,walk north,walked north,adventure,geowizard adventure,adventure series,part 1,english,england,british,british guy,tom,tom davies,staffordshire,peak district,funny,setting off,set off,simply
description:
adventure comes in many forms today we indulge in one of the simplest and purest forms of adventure there is 
join me as i grab a sleeping bag stuff a tenner in my pocket and walk north from my front door into the countryside for as long as fate sees necessary along the way we forage for food gasp for water sleep in questionable places bump into countless generous countryside folk and explore the glorious hobbitlike english countryside with a sense of childlike wonder and freedom

watch with subtitles and in 4k for best results

video_title: colossal sea monster unearthed in uk  bbc news
tags: bbc,bbc news,news,world news,breaking news,us news,world,america,usa,usa news,india news
description:
the skull of a colossal sea monster has been extracted from the cliffs of the jurassic coast in dorset uk

it belongs to a pliosaur a ferocious marine reptile that terrorised the oceans about 150 million years ago

the 2mlong fossil is one of the most complete specimens of its type ever discovered and is giving new insights into this ancient predator

the skull will be featured in a special david attenborough programme on bbc one on new years day

subscribe here httpbitly1rbfuog

for more news analysis and features visit wwwbbccomnews 

palaeontology seacreatures bbcnews

a few notes

1 the plank of wood under the car isnt actually wood its a plank of resin with titanium blocks skid blocks in certain parts of the plank this is where the sparks come from when they skid across the ground

2 kers is a bit dated  its just ers now lol thats because while there is kinetic energy recovery from braking mguk motor generator unit  kinetic there is also energy recovery from the exhaust gasses mguh motor generator unit  heat

3 drs was brought in for 2011 because with the newer cars in 2010 it was basically too difficult to overtake so this was an aid when the driver behind is within 1 second they gain access to drs to try and make the pass the regulations state that the current drs gap can be maximum of 85mm so any larger than this  disqualification

awesome video marques thanks for bringing our awesome sport to so many more people 
drs was never a feature only used by one team which then spread to others from the start 2011 it was mandated by the fia in order to counter the negative effects of dirty air when following another car and as such promote more overtaking and therefore more exciting races it could never have been developed by an individual team anyway because it wouldve represented a movable part which affected aerodynamics  something that has been banned in f1 since the 1960s
407 also a quick note to new f1 fans the halo was designed by mercedes for the fia and was built using titanium encased within carbon fibre not iron
it can withstand the weight of a doubledecker bus or the equivalent of around 12000kg
now u gotta get a sim rig going got into f1 a few years ago now and been loving it awesome video
great video marques the actual race itself was so fun
hello marques i come from germany and have been watching formula 1 for over 40 years and still love it today i give you a big applause for this video very good short but also detailed explanation of the topic i think that the future formula 1 series with andretti will have a big impact on the popularity of the sport in the usa thanks for doing this great youtube job love to see your videos 
glad that you are into f1 something not many people talk about is the skills talents and fitness level of these drivers and how they progressed through different categories before getting into the pinnacle of motorsports their offseason training is also incredibly cool
been watching f1 since 2012 i am glad you started following f1 as well as tech enthusias i am sure you will love it i think your describe it as science fair is the perfect description i always love to see how the car evolve from the start to the end of the season and you can notice how some team take design inspiration form other by looking and compare their car from different stage of the season
i was fortunate to go to a race 2 years ago i was at the end of turn 1 right after one of the fastest straights of the season it was like watching a fleet of star wars ships jumping out of hyperspace incredibly fast and then decelerating abruptly it was awesome
1235 it didnt just suck the manhole cover out of the ground it broke the cracked welds holding it in place 
it is great to see so many more people enjoying f1 now i speak from only being a fan for about a year so far and even in that time the audience is only getting bigger great video giving a breakdown of how the sport works marques
great video highlighting the geniuses behind f1

one other thing the 2020 season was delayed by 4 months due to covid but the teams utilised their engineers to help with pandemic by designing and manufacturing respiratory equipment
best f1 ever were the v10 motors i will never forget the first time i walked into catalunya circuit in spain 2005 the sound fire and energy you could literally feel coming out of those v10 engines and exhausts to this day still gives me chills when i think about it

i have been blessed to be able to attend 2 race weekends in austin for the usgp its exactly as he said nothing compares to seeing it live and in person i sat on turn 15 so just after the straight away and through turns 1213 and 14 the amount of battles i saw coming through turns just to see these cars open up and hit near top speed going into the long right hander of turn 16 was truly amazing its an experience i tell everyone they need to have at least once in their life
i give you a very high salute for explaining this to those who are new to f1 and never knew the facts you explained so perfectly you now see that it is the highest technical form of auto racing i who have been a f1 fan since my childhood seen grow a very long way great job and im so glad to see you gain interest in f1 i have always enjoyed your content from when you started

liberty medias been successful in engaging more fans in the us thats great to see

i dont mind the bigeneration i instantly assumed the 14th would become the curator  the 50th special introduced him and was stated he was the doctor who retired and now the 60th showed his origin to me the doctor  wouldnt willing retire knowing there were people out there that needed help  but now with the bigeneration 14th can retire and become the curator and live a peaceful for the doctor life and the 15th doctor can continue saving the universe
i love the idea that biregeneration was a myth meaning that tennants salt at the end of the universe also made the myth come into being
from 1966 and tom campbell in dalek invasion earth to 2023 and wilfred mott bernard cribins deserves his eternal recognition in dr who history
for me it wasnt the mention of river song that buckled my knees it was them finally acknowledging that sarah jane is gone

as this was and the spice up your life dance sequence i still have no idea what the hell bigeneration means i mean we heard from all the doctors previously in the reboot that regeneration was super dodgy but making a whole new one is not a twist i was expecting but this establishes that in a oneononehundredmillionbillionbillion chance time lords can reproduce asexually however how many times can the doctor make a copy of themselves the end fight with the toymaker had the frenetic pace of tens fight with the sycorax way back in 2006 i loved ncutis energy he really felt like a showman much more than the other doctors previously and because they said he processed his trauma fifteen seems like hes going to be a doctor who is having fun and not haunted by his dark deeds or running from lovely to hear those tones of outraged relish as you relate the numerous fixes she needs and to see as well as hear your unalloyed joy that twiggys there for you your happiness makes us happy thanks for sharing it
what a lovely tour of your new spidercraft er i mean runabout  d  shes very pretty and quirky  thanks for the indepth look  i can see why you fell in love with twiggy
david with a twinkle in his eye talking about repairing a boat the order of life is restored
love your new adventure
imagine taking this little boat out across the wash like you did a narrow boat once now that would be an adventure 
i just love your new boat and so happy that youre enjoying the canals again
if you are going to be doing any fiber glassing you could raise the level of that area in front of the outboard by a 14 inch or so to make the water funnel out the drain hole better
you are the master of telling the way it is in such a uplifting and inspiring way thanks for the promised tour i could not help smiling carefully 
thanks for the tour of the boat david  im so glad that youre back on the water and i look forward to more canal stories and updates on your improvements to  the boat  thanks for sharing  keep the videos coming and safe travels 
david you are absolutely correct it is a fun little boat it definitely has lots of potential and with the tlc  you are willing to give it it will provide years of pleasurable boating no doubt when you have completed most of the fixes youll be grinning inwardly on the canals as you skim past all those naysayers cheers for now
i suggest you put the solar panel over the engine aft and hinge it so it can fold down or angle towards the sun that would free up the hatch
a bit rough around the edges but twiggy is full of potential 
obviously youre going to relocate the electrics under the hob and fit a water tank under the sink  as for matching the color after repairs i wouldnt sweat that and just have the entire boat repainted which would cover a multitude of sins enough advice you enjoy a challenge and youre quite good at fashioning solutions so have at it and enjoy your new boat
thanks david for your tour of twiggy no repairs you cant handle and it will be fun as always watching you fix it up and make it your own thanks again and keep smiling
davids trying his best to play the curmudgeon while pointing out all the things that need fixing but we all know that inside hes rubbing his hands together excitedly in anticipation of all the diy projects he gets to enjoy in bringing twiggy up to ctc standards  just as were all rubbing our hands together excitedly in anticipation of all the videos hes going to make while engaging in said diy projects  

youve got a great boat with a lot of potential and were looking forward to seeing your progress  thanks for sharing
the thing i like about this boat is that while it is certainly a project it is also perfectly functional  plenty of stuff that needs doing but on days when you dont feel like doing you can just go happily mess about in your boat thank you for the lovely tour

on a side note it is rather nice to occasionally see other people asking but why when theyre working on something old  ive been working on my old farmhouse for a number of years and i still come across things that make me wonder what the previous owners were thinking
buy a water bladder for the water supply  it will conform to the space that you have available and you can fill it with a hose from a dockside tap  if you relocate the battery bank to the opposite side they should counter balance one another
hi david  it is very good to see you back on the water  a place you are meant to be  especially with a boat needing quite a bit of handymanning  we always enjoy your videos showing how you overcome all problems with a bit of thought a few materials and stuff you buy from amazon  its diy as an art form  that combined with your excellent storytelling great use of video and deadpan humour makes our day  thank you
im trying to image the proud owners on their first day taking delivery of this little vessel and what an exciting time it would have been
im loving this reminds me of a boat my wife and i went to look at some years ago except that yours is immaculate in comparison it actually steers reasonably without constantly spinning the wheel left and right like a lunatic to try and keep it straight looking forward to the next episode

top_comments:
congratulations jaiden on having grandchildren 
the fortune tellers saying jaiden would have 3 kids is suddenly making a lot more sense
good job ari and tofu woooo lets goooo
check out the scribble after dark tour grab tickets here  httpscribbleshowdowncom
i cant believe we witnessed jaiden growing up so fast first a college student now a grandmother
if you want to keep the eggs and want to move them out of the freezer you can also encase them in resin as a memento of her laying eggs without running the risk of accidentally breaking them in the freezer or having them explode cause normal eggs can explode in the freezer and idk if it would be harder or easier to explode tiny eggs like that
if you go back and watch aris first birthday theres a great segment that goes along the lines of  i dont know aris gender the only way to really know is a dna test unless its too late and you already have eggs everywhere
for anyone wondering there are two types of birds nesting and nonnesting a nesting birds babies are called nestlings and when first hatched are super fragile needs constant food cannot walk or fly is completely featherless and takes longer to mature a nonnesting birds babies are just called chicks and when first hatched can walk dont need constant food cannot fly and has a fuzzy coat that keeps them warm independantly of their mother

chickens turkeys quail pheasants ducks geese etc all give birth to chicks which is why you may be thinking that baby birds are easy to care for they kinda just figure out life on their own nestling birds need special equipment foods and sometimes medicines to be raised by humans you need to feed them every 46 hours with a syringe keep them warm and keep them hydrated which is harder to do when they are kept warm for the duration of their infancy you basically have to nap instead of sleep or have a second person assist you as you both plan your sleep schedules to do a 1212 shift you need to take care of them for something or rather every 3 hours on the hour raising a bird seems really cool but dont raise a nestling unless you know everything about the species you are trying to raise
tip if you want to know if the eggs are fertilized or not just put a flashlight over them and look if there is any red spots over the yellow gold
jaiden i hope they get along
the birds bubble gum electric
as a female cockatiel owner egg binding is a scary concept ive been told calcium supplements and a vet visit to remove any stuck eggs is fine but still so sols cage has no possible nesting spots and when shes out of it shes always with me so its all good  

sol is such a personable sweetheart i adore her she demands head scritches from everyone including the vet lol and hates hates hates raisins like will literally throw them out of her feed hates them learned that the first time when i was hand feeding her bits of her feed and she bounced it off my knee xd

as for the sawdust comment i can 100 believe that sol had a toy meant for the parakeets my twin and i used to have before they passed but never ended up giving it to and she adored it she cronched that thing like cookie wafer  sounded like it too anyway the moment it stopped being an out of cage toy and i hung it up inside said cage it got absolutely demolished very quickly and there was just woodchips everywhere so many woodchips i swear the thing should not have produced that many but it did

i adore birds theyre my favorite kind of pet but i am very consciously aware that a cockatiel is my best match and not say a conure or heaven forbid an actual parrot and thats okay also jaiden is 110 correct raising baby birds is a nightmare i wouldve done the same thing as would many other bird owners google it if you dont believe us back on topic though while in my opinion birds make for the best kind of pet you need to take into account whether or not you are able to give them the time and attention they need know what you can and cannot do and if you cant thats okay know your limits but dont get a bird if you cant take care of it properly itll just end in tears 

so to sum it up egg binding is scary sol is the best sorry not sorry ari and tofu bird sawdust is real raising baby birds is a nightmare and birds make for the best pets if and only if youre able to meet their needs and theres nothing wrong with you if you cant just dont get a bird if so
pray for jaden that she doesnt lose her mind from taking care of lots of birds
as an er vet who sees birds i agree with 100 of your sentiments about bird ownership at the end loved the video very humorous but also spreading the truth about bird ownership
my friend had three parakeets in the past the mother died naturally and then the daughter unalived her father glad to see tofu and ari are well 
i love jaidens pet videos about her feathered babies hopefully she makes one for tostada the kitty cat one day too
015 i just wanna mention how nice this depiction of this fanbase is all just calmly cheering for ari i love this depiction because fans of any media these days sometimes are portrayed as rabidly obsessed creatures with no sense of reason and it hurts when youre part of that fanbase it really shows the maturity of her team and of jaidens fans i commend you all this really is such a lovely mature and respectful community
as a long time fan this is crazy to watch never would i have thought ari would become a dad or a mom
as a cat owner of the most gremlin crazy cats i laughed so hard at this video pet owners of the pets who destroy things but who you love dearly truly understand where youre coming from 
as a green cheek conure owner piccolo and bansuri are some of the best things that ever happened to me i regret nothing and simultaneously theyre the bane of my existence
my friend had three parakeets in the past the mother died naturally and then the daughter unalived her father glad to see tofu and ari are well

video_title: hunting for water  gold to revive my abandoned ghost town
tags: Cerro Gordo,Ghost Town,Gold Prospecting,Water Exploration,Abandoned Places,Historic Mines,Treasure Hunt,Ghost Town Life,Cerro Gordo Adventures,Cerro Gordo Exploration,Ghost Town Series,Urban Exploration,Mining History,Cerro Gordo Projects,Cerro Gordo Update,Abandoned Towns,Cerro Gordo Progress,Water Witches,Water Dowsing
description:
hello there this past month was a great one up here at cerro gordo we had a lot of experts come to look for things like water gold and wood we made progress on a lot of projects and even started some new ones 

thank you all so so much for all the support over the years it means the world to me

check out jason at mbmmllc and dan at danhurd 

also  i wrote a book i have been working on this for almost two years now and i am so excited to finally announce it i put my put my heart and soul into this thing and really dug deep on making sense of these past 3 years living up here the book has all sorts of new stories insights and history of the town i think its the best content ive ever made

if youve ever got anything out of this channel i hope youll consider preordering the book it is a huge way to show support for everything going on and would mean the world to me 

amazon httpswwwamazoncomgpproduct0593578449
barnes  noble signed copies httpsbitly3qrzoyb
booksamillion httpsbitly3tnauks
bookshoporg httpsbitly3rzb5bn

available in all formats  hardcover ebook and audio httpswwwpenguinrandomhousecombooks709605ghosttownlivingbybrentunderwood

if you do preorder the book before jan 1 2024 i have some special bonuses for you 

 buy 1 book and get unreleased pages from the book and an unreleased full video of some of the best mine exploration ive never shown 
 buy 5 books and ill send you a signed page from the draft manuscript for you to have

 forward all receipts of the book to bookcerrogordominescom 

for more behind the scenes photos check out my instagram httpswwwinstagramcombrentwunderwood

merch cerro gordo tshirts and more httpsstorecerrogordominescom 

mailing address po box 490 lone pine ca 93545

for shorter videos from around cerro gordo check out my second channel httpswwwyoutubecomghosttown2

video_title: baby seal drags bucket
tags: Ocean Conservation Namibia,Plastic Pollution,Namibia,Conservation,Animal Rescue,Pelican Point,Leatherman,Walvis Bay,Ocean Pollution,Namib_Naude,Seal Rescue,Sea Lion,Pollution,GoPro,Cape Cross,Naude Dreyer,Fishing line,Seal Baby,seal pup,Skeleton Coast,Seal,100sealsfortime,NGO Namibia,Injured Seal,Ghostnet,Sea lion rescue,baby seal rescue,injured sea lion,seals namibia,pinnipeds,rescue net,stemthetide,entanglement,seaspiracy,swakopmund,gill net
description:
unbelievable the line was so tight around the seals neck and not cutting it yet seeing the seal fill up with air after the last line was cut was such a huge relief there are many reasons why this seal would not have made it back to shore for example with water getting in the bucket etc every time we find such mindboggling entanglements it raises immense concern about how many animals never make it so this baby seal is really lucky

about demon slayer kimetsu no yaiba
demon slayer kimetsu no yaiba is based on the manga series by koyoharu gotoge published under shueishas jump comics which consists of 23 volumes and over 150 million copies in publication the animation production is by ufotable

the story begins when tanjiro kamado a boy whose family is killed by a demon joins the demon slayer corps to turn his younger sister nezuko back into a human after she is transformed into a demon in april 2019 the tv anime series demon slayer kimetsu no yaiba first premiered with the tanjiro kamado unwavering resolve arc followed by the release of the feature film mugen train in october 2020 and the tv series mugen train arc and entertainment district arc from october 2021 and the swordsmith village arc from april 2023 in spring 2024 the new longawaited tv series hashira training arc will premiere

video_title: chris harris on the 1990 williamsrenault fw13b formula one car  hungarian grand prix winner
description:
this is one for all you f1 fans out there as an introduction for its arrival on private sales by collecting cars chris harris dives into the archives with former head of williams heritage jonathan williams to discuss the history of the grand prix winning 1990 williamsrenault fw13b formula 1 car 

this car is now available on private sales by collecting cars httpscollectingcarscomforsale1990williamsrenaultfw13b

with a striking design that any aesthete can appreciate the fw1313b model is a particularly notable racer from williams history claiming three grand prix wins across the 1989 and 1990 seasons that achievement is all the more impressive considering the dominance of senna and prost over those two years between them winning 21 of the 32 races

chassis fw13b08 is arguably the most impressive of all securing not only pole position in qualifying but taking its driver to outright victory at the hungaroring in 1990 leading from start to finish

finding a car that has spent 25 years in its teams private collection is unusual but another factor that makes this chassis especially rare is that it retains the original renault rs2 35litre v10 most of these powertrains were scrapped in period so it is remarkable to find a car still running its correct and fully functional works engine

video_title: incredible chiefs td on travis kelces lateral waved off for offsides
tags: nfl,nfl espn,espn nfl,nfl on espn,nfl news,football,national football league,nfl 2023,espn,#nfl,#espn
description:
watch as wr kadarius toney lines up offside and costs the kansas city chiefs a goahead touchdown against the buffalo bills in the final minutes of the game

 subscribe to espn httpespnpluscomyoutube
 get the espn app httpwwwespncomespnappsespn

top_comments:
congratulations bills you beat the chiefs and made them cry its a win for all football fans
now he knows what its like to play the chiefs 
the call was 100 correct chiefs have no one to blame but themselves
for those who didnt watch snf tonight

this penalty was called once in 2021 twice last year and 11 times coming into the game this season 

so it was obviously a point of emphasis for officials and the flag was thrown immediately upon the snap so it wasnt some conspiracy 

mahomes reaction is really rubbing me wrong and comes off spoiled
there has been a lot of bad officiating this season 

this was an example of good officiating
hes looking at the baaaaaaaall  and still line up off sidewow
chiefs are arguing that such a ticky tack call shouldnt happen at such an important point of the game  we should go back and see what the eagles think about the holding call in the super bowl last year chiefs werent complaining then
never understood why any player whatever the position would line up offside  these guys have been playing this game their whole lives and are the best at what they do  you dont even have to move your bod just use a couple of neck muscles turn your head and look  unbelievable
because the chiefs have gotten so many favorable calls over the years mahomes wanted all the spotlight to go on him the bills won this game and they dont even get to be applauded for it because the only thing that people are going to be remembering from this game is this play where the penalty was rightly called mahomes does not need to get mad at the refs he needs to get mad at his receiver for lining up offsides
all penalties aside that was a sweet lateral 
still one of the best plays seen this year to bad toney didnt look where he was standing
if youre lined up as a receiver and you have to look back over your shoulder around the defensive lineman standing next to you to see the ball  youre offsides  how did toney not realize the ball and center was behind him
doesnt matter how many times it was called before you know the rules offsides is offsides end of story he could have just as easily went to the line and moved his foot back a few inches he knew the game was at stake and if he didnt know he was offsides then the person next to him should have known
he was looking right at the ball how could he not know to move back thats on him
whats shocking is that toney didnt drop the lateral from kelce
all penalties aside that was a sweet lateral
ive always wondered why back laterals werent used more they are used effectively in flag football i know theres no contact so its a bit easier but if done correctly there is alot of open plays for tds like this one
as a broncos fan it puts joy in my heart seeing him like this
it does look like offsides but what a cool play the chiefs are an amazing team
geez that was a great throw a great catch and an amazing pass ending with an exciting td would have been fun in highlight reels kelce probably cant reenact that lastsecond pass what a shame

3920 first time in japan over twenty years ago taught me that rice is not a bulk up  filler  meal item but  something to be enjoyed as much as any other item on the plate even in something as texturally and flavour diverse as a shojin ryori meal the rice is as much a part of the experience and been mildly evangelical about spreading that opinion  its a hard sell to a lot of westerners

touch ball mice are used a lot in north america canada more then usa they are used a lot for work in fields that use programs such as autocad maya blender and image creation such as krita photoshop etc they work very well for a lot of things even gaming i loved mine but the ball has a small accident exactly like the one you had when you picked it up my sister and i nicked named the ball  booots its a joke from baldurs gate 2 with the gigantic minatare space hamster and when it would fall out of the rest of the mouse it was one of those moments of almost yelling no boots as if fell and if it hits something hard or even a pointy pebble and gets a scratch on its all over its done and now you are sad i would buy another one should they drop in price as they became more rare in stores and the reason that is important is unlike a mouse that you can usually find a way to hold relatively weird mice with ball mice you need to make sure it fits your hand in a very comfortable way while you control the ball with your thumb so it makes sure you can do that for extended amount of time so if it does not fit your hand right you will hate it with a passion when it fits right you wonder why you have not been using this type of mouse for your whole life so you need to make sure its the right fit for you and make sure you never drop the ball as that is how boots died one little scratch and the dream was dead but got i believe 4 years out of her before that unfortunate accident after that time no stores were carrying them except one and it was a crap one and a very shitty size and quality 
final thing there are some that use 24 optical sensors that make it be able to do much more control in a 3d environment such as 123d autocad and others but it also makes games such as mmorpgs fps and rts a joy to play and target with insane accuracy for headshots especially the multiple sensor ones

so find the right one that fits your hand and has the amount of sensors you want with the dpi you want and never look back that said you should still have a normal mouse as sometimes if your hand is tired or your thumb is soar or something like that a normal mouse can be a little easier to use for those moments

video_title: feasters microwave burgers  ashens
tags: ashens food,taste test,convenience food,food review uk,food special,fast food,microwave burger,microwaveable burger,ashens food review,microwave burgers,hot dog,ashens,review,funny,sausage bap
description:
late pledges for horror film possible yes httpturnbackmoviecom
burgers and microwaves together again in our hearts or more to the point our arteries
previously a dark combination of damp spongey bread and reheated mashedup cow flesh theyve improved over the years mostly by telling you to toast the bun now weve got some superbudget microwaveable snacks  burger sausage and hot dog  to look at so er lets do that

microwave burger ashens
top_comments:
nothing beats a classic ashens food special 
ah ashens once again showing his enlightened hotdog technique
wow ashens is really dedicated to travel all the way from dans place in redacted to norwich and back just for some microwave burgers
i mean for 90p its definitely a better option than rustlers which used to be cheapish and are now basically as much as a proper sandwich
crazy how you could make both an advent video with dan and this on the same day crazy
627
you can see the bun slowly reinflating itself as ashens positively remarks on the taste
ive had these before the cheapest feasters yellow packaging are disgusting but the more expensive ones red packaging are actually very nice
for some reason ive been binge watching these videos and i literally cannot distinguish between a 9 year old video and a brand new one
thankfully ashens aged better than most of the food in his videos 
you put the mustard on that hotdog perfectly
as an asda employee i see feasters come through the tills quite often i shall now forever think of ashens everytime i see one
only ashens could have me enthusiastic about looking at feasters
hotdogs marketed specifically as microwave hotdogs have always confused me bread rolls arent expensive and its not like you cant do a normal hotdog in the microwave
oh microwaved hotdogs one of the things i never thought i would miss from going to grandmas after school shes still alive and i am a grown hairy arsed man man just no one told me id have to watch her slowly lose her memories and herself i hope she goes quietly without pain
feasters is just the brand name asda uses instead of rustlers for its microwave burgers theyre exactly the same
feasters will use ashens quotes in their promotional materials for the sausage bap like you can tell theres something in there and its not superunpleasant
for me the aldi version of these is my fave price measured against taste theyre a godsend as a midnight snack after erm yknow a few wobbly imbibements saved me a fortune on impulsive dirty takeaways
from my long experience working at call centres the number 1 use case for this sort of thing is for when youve got a 30 minute lunch break and tesco ready meals want a full 8 of those minutes in the microwave plus cooling time
it doesnt look terrible too be honest these kinds of burgers and sandwiches are kind of a guilty pleasure of mine ive made many an acceptably agreeable breakfast out of the odd microwave burger
stuart is eating food that hasnt expired im impressed
when i was in the uk living for a while i was that poor with my wife that we ate nothing but home made pancakes made with water flour and sugar for 5 months every meal these would have been perfect

top_comments:
when the npcs are glitching out like that then try talking to them first  if that doesnt work then continue doing what youre doing
one thing i like about the prefab builds is theyre modular you can knock out the walls on a double shack and replace them with shack doors to create passible outbuildings
biggest building issue ive had is there doesnt seem to be a way to change the elevation of your nonprefab foundations making it hard to keep things at the same level
destroying bushes is actually easier with a sword
for me rn traveling is the main issue it cant be that u have to walk 10 mins just to get to a cave once u mined the 2 caves kinda nearby your village or walk 20 mins to the next dessert just so you can die bcs u didnt know that the mobs there are way stronger
you can also build campfires inside of caves instead of using torches  yes it costs more wood however itll light up the cave for you so its easier to find whatever your looking for
before commenting understand that deliberately exploiting is cheating not a tip
dont just throw away tools that you dont use use a villager as a follower and you can give them those tools and they will use it they can hold multiple tools and just swap to the best one depending on the situation
really fantastic synopsis and tips you nailed it i would add 
build your first village at the edge of a desert border and near a knotwood cave not where you spawn into the game make your life easier and everything more efficient
build a bed at the mouth of a cave as a save point if you die you respawn in your bed you wont have to travel back to your quest point
empty almost all of your backpack before beginning a quest youll need the inventory slots
pack for a trip max wood planks to build repair chests cooked food snowberry shakes or cheesy burgers
its good to stack lumber mills it makes crafting so much quicker
something i always do with the spare pickaxes is give it to one designated adventuring villager and whenever i need to collect granite i take that villager and start going at some rocks unfortunately they still use the pickaxes for fighting even over axes even tho the brown pickaxe does less damage per second compared to just punching so keep that in mind if ur messing about in the dark with them
if you find a boulder on a hill and you need mats just push the boulder down hill towards whatever you need and itll destroy everything for you
go on top of moutains that have large trees cut them down roll the log down to farm granite and wood super easy
i love to make a village stylish and neat it is the most important thing 
man this was one of the coolest surprises of the year  ive always thought a minecraft style game in the lego world would be awesome  whod have thought it would be fortnite to do it
youre lucky  the desert is a 10 minute run away from my spawn point and thats with infinite stamina  however the cold biome is 2 steps away
make glider  build staircases 11 high make platform and u now got a jump pad that will take u way further then the geysers and as soon as i land i build another one so i can basically do the whole map under 10 mins instead of an hour lol i even put a marker on every staircase jump pad so i know the direction they follow back to back  helps tons on the map
stamina bar is important when youre flying with a glider it consumes your stamina while up in the air by the time you run out you will drop from fall damage and die
i personally think temp dont matter as muchbut stam will literally make you op in the beginning bc u can just outrun most early in things like wolves
i noticed when you broke your grill the village points didnt go down so technically ig you could just place down a crap ton of grills lumber mills work benches etc then destroy them to get the materials back and do it again and again
the way i get the sand shells is by using a shield and getting one of my villagers to follow me that way my follower can get the attention and i can go ham for the shells and the shield helps if the randomly start going for you

top_comments:
new bad coffee trend drink only positively charged coffee grounds throw away the identical negative charged grounds
i am absolutely certain that if 1 of humanity increased the level of interest and passion in what they did regardless of what that may be to even a fraction of what you do with and for coffee the world would be a much better place
thank you james for encouraging people through coffee to do more do better and question what they do
the reason youre not seeing particle size differences in your particle sized analyser is probably because it breaks up the electroclumps during the measuring process no idea the details of how the machine works but it would be far from surprising if it was violent enough to the micron sized particles to break up the electroclumps into their constituent grains
its fascinating that the spritzing makes a measurable difference to the extraction of the espresso i could totally see well in theory this should have a marginal benefit but in reality itll probably never mean anything but its amazing that they were able to actually measure a meaningful quantitative change
i love the citizen science your channel is promoting and that youre encouraging mixed and unclear results to be shared there is a signal here we just cant see it yet keep sharing keep signal boosting and keep experimenting
if you close your eyes you can experience what its like to have jon hamm describe coffee physics to you
i think when collecting data from lots of people tracking relative humidity in the air might be really important i keep my house really dry 30 for 3d printing and i see a massive amount of static cling on my grinder which doesnt have any bottleneck so rh may be a significant source of noise
im not sure why the links arent showing for some people here they are

the google survey 
httpsformsgleaggetuddcnquvrzr7
the paper direct link httpsbitlywetbeans
supplemental paper httpsbitlycoffeestatic
its always a pleasure to watch these videos and even more of a pleasure to watch james slowly transition from barista to a coffee research scientist with his own laboratory
decided to try this again after giving up on misting beans ages ago  somehow forgot that id since repurposed the atomizer for adding orange blossom water to homemade orgeat  while i cant endorse deliberately using orange blossom water in your coffee grinder it certainly made for an interesting espresso and a real proustian moment while i played what the hell is that weird perfume flavor
my suggestion for the slowing flow rate would be that the coating of water on all the coffee particles drastically increases the capillary action of the coffee bed which usually i would think is fairly hydrophobic if dry the oils in the coffee also probably dont help with that if you try to water dry soil versus slightly damp soil you see the effect of a thin water coating makes orders of magnitude of difference so a stronger capillary force from the already present water allows the coffee to be drawn into the packed bed more evenly and reduces the chances of channels forming leading to higher leaching rates and slower flow rates this is not contrary to what the prof said it might be a combination of both
even though im not that into coffee and usually just guess each time i make it i absolutely love your videos its not just the information but the candor the dedication without obsession and the curiosity i wish there were clones of you making youtube videos on different topics  itd be a better world
this is fascinating  theres a nugget here about grinding frozen coffee  ive been freezing beans for freshness since i use coffee pretty slowly  an unintended result is that when i take out a dose of 18 grams of beans to grind pretty quickly they get covered in a nice even layer of condensation because they are so cold  its like getting a mist and mix for no effort  hard to control the amount which is a function of time and the relative humidity in the room but interesting nonetheless  ive also had no issues with grinding frozen beans in my breville barista express or my fellow ode gen 1 and not surprisingly ive had much less issue with static compared to grinding room temperature beans in the same grinders
man this video is surreal i dont think i ever had a chance to meet him specifically but i was just at a small conference with chris hendon a few months ago and met several of his students and heard a bit about his coffee research i dont think ive ever seen someone ive encountered so closely in such a popular piece of media as this i suspected that he or his work about coffee though he also studies wine and other compounds more relevant to industrial chemistry would show up here eventually though super exciting stuff
i am super excited that you got a particle size analyzer and from a legit analytical science company like anton paar that is an incredible leap towards quantifying the impact of different grinders burrs grind rpm etc which so far has been limited to assumptions wow that instrument is a significant investment too and im thrilled you got to a place where your fame and fortune so to speak can be put towards advanced coffee science to benefit all weird coffee people everywhere

im assuming well be seeing a lot of grinder studies now using that instrument cant wait 
i used this spritzing water method a few weeks back before this paper was published my grinder is the new fellow opus it was the first time i did it with the opus because i never thought of doing it since the grinder has anti static tech and i was so surprised that when wet it took vastly much longer to reach 36g than when its dry now that this paper has been published im going to try it again
james i would love if you could get a multimeter and measure the resistance of the various materials the griders are constructed from particularly where the machines directly contact the ground coffee at the end of the grind my theory is that more conductive surfaces like metals will better dissipate the charges than plastic insulators i think this likely accounts for that initial difference you noticed between different grinders  the eureka mignon oro has a metal spout and cup
i just tried spritzing for pour over coffee there was less static cling which was nice i also noticed that the water drained through the coffee grounds a bit slower i only did it once so it could be a fluke
well done chris and his fellow authors as well as you james what shocks me is that there isnt more science on how to improve the taste of coffee probably because the perception of taste is subjectively measured rather than objectively but there seems to be so much scope to improve brewing and roasting techniques
just a simple thank you james for all you do endlessly fascinating to me and rewarding every time i make my coffee

video_title: sabertooth vs raptor who would win
description:
this is the first of a new series im calling the anachrolab an animated series depicting fights between species who normally were separated by millions of years this pilot episode took two years to produce the next episode is already underway and will hopefully take a bit less time to create

video_title: starship  second flight test
description:
on november 18 2023 starship successfully lifted off at 702 am ct from starbase on its second integrated flight test 

while it didnt happen in a lab or on a test stand it was absolutely a test what we did with this second flight will provide invaluable data to continue rapidly developing starship 

the test achieved a number of major milestones helping us improve starships reliability as spacex seeks to make life multiplanetary the team at starbase is already working final preparations on the vehicles slated for use in starships third flight test 

congratulations to the entire spacex team on an exciting second flight test of starship

follow us on xcomspacex for continued updates on starships progress

video_title: the casting of frank stone  reveal trailer
tags: dead by daylight,dbd,behaviour interactive,bhvr,slasher game,survival horror,the casting of frank stone,supermassive games,tcofs,frank stone
description:
wishlist now httpsdbdgame3slyvdo 

the storytelling prowess of supermassive games meets the dead by daylight universe in a haunting horror game that wont soon be forgotten

the shadow of frank stone looms over cedar hills a town forever altered by his violent past as a group of young friends are about to discover stones bloodsoaked legacy cuts deep leaving scars across families generations and the very fabric of reality itself  

in the depths of an oregon steel mill the gruesome crimes of a sadistic killer spawn horrors beyond comprehension delve into the mystery of cedar hills alongside an original cast of characters bound together on a twisted journey where nothing is quite as it seems  

every decision you make shapes the story and impacts the fate of the characters within it brimming with emotional gutpunches and highstakes horror discover how a simple decision can become a truly heartwrenching dilemma

for those who find comfort in the unknown and glee in the grotesque supermassive games cinematic storytelling brings new levels of emotion immersion and intensity to this darkly rich universe

experience a neverbeforeseen look at the wider world of dead by daylight behaviour interactives acclaimed multiplayer horror game filled with spinechilling twists this dark original tale is certain to haunt you long after its over

coming 2024

follow the casting of frank stone
httpswwwinstagramcomcastingfrankstone 
httpstwittercomtcofrankstone

tcofs dbd
top_comments:
for people who are confused

this is a brand new single player game set in the dbd universe featuring as far as we know original characters who will likely come to dbd as skins or characters in the future this is made in collaboration with supermassive games who are known to be behind until dawn the quarry and the dark pictures anthology this game will likely be in a style where the player makes choices that will alter the story it will release sometime in 2024

by the way the song is daylight by david kushner
this game has gone so far its insane
it actually looks so good more dead by daylight lore i cant wait
this could be supermassives best game since until dawn well done to both companies im excited  
i love how his helmet is shaped like entitys jaws solid way to reveal more about the character through his design
something about seeing from the world of dead by daylight with solemn music in the background is emotional like for the past 7 years excitement around dead by daylight had always been about what outside thing they brought in like license chapters for the first time hype is generated by someone else announcing that they are collaborating with dead by daylight im also so excited to be able to see dead by daylight in a more cinematic lense finally being able to properly experience the horror of dbd
theres a lot of symbolism in the name the casting of frank stone frank stoke being some form of character casting either being casted by the entity for what we know as the trials or casting in terms of being shaped or molded by the entity as well as casting and stone in the title could imply the saying casting the first stone so this may very well be some form of beginning to the story we know this may have been where the first stone of our story is casted
i like how the killer already looks so unsure about what he wants to do and what hes becoming and when hes shown off in the mask it looks like hes just exhausted and so regretful of whatever deal he made with the entity
you guys have no idea how happy i am to see you two collab together cant wait for this game
if they really want this to feel special i hope we also get to make choices from the killer pov remember that most killers are as much victims of the entity as the survivors and want to escape this purgatory
some hunches i have about this game

1 this could possibly be the first killer that arrived in the entities realm and tells the story about how he got there before being tossed into the void
2 the screams in the background are most likely the four main characters being held captive by said killer who at some point during the game manage to escape and you have to help them make it out alive 
3 the entitys full physical form is seen for the first time that being a gigantic spider while it is said that the realm itself is the entity ex trees birds pallets etc on the official dbd wiki it states that the entities most preferred form is that of a spider resembling something from stephen kings it 
4 its my strong hunch that whoever it is that is supposed to canonically survive the game will most likely show up as a future survivor in the core game 

all in all im really excited for this game cant wait to get my hands on it

edit when i was looking at the steam page for the game i also noticed a pharmaceutical store that had afterpiece tonic on it so well probably get to meet a younger version of the clown at some point or maybe a close relative that refers to him

edit 2 did some thinking and i believe that we will experience the 4 main characters get taken by the entity which will result in them encountering frank stone and we will experience a full trial in a more cinematic perspective this would explain why his workbench is covered in nature by the time the others show up so before that happens its really more so getting to know the towns history and the scars frank left behind
this is an infinitely more interesting collaboration than i thought it was going to be would be super fun to get some outfits or even chapters related to their other games
felt a surprising amount of emotion from this trailer very well made
you can see the reference from the song itself frank doesnt really want to kill but hes being forced by the entity

hiding all of our sins from the daylight  his eyes speaks from the sins he committed such a powerful trailer indeed
im crying seeing how far and how much dead by daylight has grown and i get a shot of nostalgia whenever i play this game
finally expanding the dbd franchise in a way that makes the most sense not everyone likes 4v1s but a lot of people like horror based story games 

imagine new characters or existing characters story fleshed out in an interactive way 

this is a good sign
this has to be one of my favorite trailers you guys have made the music the animation its just great
for anyone wondering what the gameplay and chase sequences will be like

most of the game is cutscenes where you make choices that determine events that happen and who livesdies all action sequences during the game are also cutscenes with things like quick time events for example if you had to jump over a pallet to escape the killer in the game a buttom would appear on the screen if you press the button before it vanishes you jump over the pallet if you dont then the character is either permenantly dead or lives through luck somehow the rest of the gameplay while not being chased will basically be 3rd person and you will just walk around through areas finding clues and trying to escape

also if you want more games like this check out until dawn the quarry and the 4 games in the dark picture anthology
this trailer is a masterpiece this music and this camera optics
perfect music choice i am so in this has to be one of the best directed trailers for anything i have ever seen well done on both companies you guys knocked it out of the park

video_title: lego fortnite gameplay trailer
description:
explore vast open worlds where the magic of lego building and fortnite collide
collect food and resources craft items build shelter and battle enemies solo or team up with up to seven friends

get creative in building and customizing your ultimate home base using lego elements collected from the world around you then recruit villagers to gather materials and help survive the night gear up and drop into deep caves in search of rare resources and hidden areas 

find the ultimate survival crafting lego adventure in fortnite the journey is only just beginning with new world building gameplay features and more lego style outfits arriving in updates starting early 2024

description:
welcome back to stick to football with gary neville jamie carragher ian wright and roy keane  the original show from the awardwinning the overlap brought to you by sky bet

the panel kickoff the show with a secret santa draw with jill scott already making her pick and absent from the episode the five will return in a special christmas episode with their secret gifts

gary and jamie respond to manchester city manager pep guardiolas press conference quotes following garys suggestion that city have become complacent and talk about how arsenal are hitting the right form as they head into the festive fixtures

stick to football also reacts to the latest offfield issues at manchester united after former player nemanja matic revealed who and why teammates were fined listen to how gary ian jamie and roy all dealt with club punishments during their professional career

super 6 is back with ben has gary kept up his sizeable lead or has roy managed to claw some ground back

and we have your community questions find out the biggest sacrifice gary had to make as a teenager who had just left school and which player made ians introduction to football incredibly difficult

description:
when we were writing this we were very much writing about a characterand it wasnt until two days later that i was like this is me billie eilish and finneas take us through a very intimate journey inside of their creative minds as they unveil how they created their soundtrack for the movie barbie from the physics involved in the intricate production elements to billies heartbroken yet powerful delivery the duo dissects every step behind bringing their hauntingly beautiful song to life 

still havent subscribed to vanity fair on youtube  httpbitly2z6ya9m

want to stay in the know subscribe to vanity fair magazine and be exquisitely informed  httpvntyfrcom2ruqgw2

about vanity fair
arts and entertainment business and media politics and world affairsvanity fairs features and exclusive videos capture the people places and ideas that define modern culture

video_title: tesla cybertruck v lamborghini urus drag race
tags: carwow,mat watson,car review,new car review,car review 2023,new car 2023,tesla,tesla cybertruck,cybertruck,cyber truck,tesla cyber truck,cybertruck drag race,cybertruck hp,cybertruck bhp,cybertruck performance,tesla cybertruck drag race,electric suv,electric pick-up,electric pick-up truck,lambo,lamborghini,lamborghini urus,urus,lambo urus,lamborghini urus drag race,lambo urus drag race,urus drag race,cybertruck v urus
description:
welcome to the ultimate petrol vs electric drag race 

weve got our hands on the allnew tesla cybertruck and its lining up alongside the a lamborghini urus but which will come out on top  petrol or electric 

well lets check out the stats starting with the cybertruck it rolls up equipped with three electric motors and they combine to produce 845hp and 930nm of torque the starting price of the dualmotor edition is around 49000 but for this trimotor cyberbeast edition itll cost you around 96000 in terms of weight the cybertruck tips the scales at just over 3 tonnes it also has a top speed of 130mph 

then we have the lambo its packing a 4litre twinturbo v8 under the bonnet and this can produce 650hp and 850nm of torque power is sent to all four wheels via an 8speed torque converter gearbox and its a whole lot lighter than the tesla tipping the scales at 2200kg it also has a much bigger top speed coming in at 190mph 

so the cybertruck has the urus beat when it comes to performance stats but will the extra weight drag it down theres only one way to find out for sure lets race

description:
in november of 2022 ken block and the hoonigan team headed to mexico city mx to film the next installment of the electrikhana series with the audi s1 hoonitron just over one month later the devastating loss of ken block meant that the project was shelved  until now

block the hoonigans and audi continue pushing the limits of whats possible in the performance ev world with electrikhana two sliding through iconic areas of mexico city in blocks infamously aggressive rallyinspired driving style improving the car immediately after the first film block and audi built on important development lessons from their experience in las vegas

a big thank you goes out to the partners who helped make electrikhana two possible

video_title: masters of the air  official trailer  apple tv
tags: masters of the air,master of the air,trailer,trailers,masters of the air trailer,official trailer,masters of the air official trailer,austin butler,masters of the air austin butler,callum turner,anthony boyle,nate mann,raff law,barry keoghan,josiah cross,branden cook,steven spielberg,tom hanks,gary goetzman,series,masters of the air apple tv,adaptation,apple tv,apple,tv,apple tv+,apple tv plus,apple tv app,apple original,world war II,world war
description:
from the executive producers of band of brothers and the pacific comes masters of the air the 9part series event premieres january 26 httpsapplecomastersoftheair

based on donald l millers book of the same name and scripted by john orloff masters of the air follows the men of the 100th bomb group the bloody hundredth as they conduct perilous bombing raids over nazi germany and grapple with the frigid conditions lack of oxygen and sheer terror of combat conducted at 25000 feet in the air portraying the psychological and emotional price paid by these young men as they helped destroy the horror of hitlers third reich is at the heart of masters of the air some were shot down and captured some were wounded or killed and some were lucky enough to make it home regardless of individual fate a toll was exacted on them all

the series features a stellar cast led by academy award nominee austin butler callum turner anthony boyle and nate mann who are joined by raff law academy award nominee barry keoghan josiah cross branden cook and ncuti gatwa

hailing from apple studios masters of the air is executive produced by steven spielberg through amblin television and tom hanks and gary goetzman for playtone amblin televisions darryl frank and justin falvey coexecutive produce alongside playtones steven shareshian in addition to writing orloff coexecutive produces graham yost also serves as coexecutive producer anna boden  ryan fleck cary joji fukunaga dee rees and tim van patten serve as directors
