video_title: handson with gemini interacting with multimodal ai
description:
gemini is our natively multimodal ai model capable of reasoning across text images audio video and code this video highlights some of our favorite interactions with gemini learn more and try the model httpsdeepmindgooglegemini 

explore our prompting approaches here httpsgooglehowitsmadegemini 

for the purposes of this demo latency has been reduced and gemini outputs have been shortened for brevity

subscribe to our channel httpswwwyoutubecomgoogle
tweet with us on twitter httpstwittercomgoogle
follow us on instagram httpswwwinstagramcomgoogle
join us on facebook httpswwwfacebookcomgoogle

000 intro
019 multimodal dialogue
132 multilinguality
204 game creation
231 visual puzzles
317 making connections
339 image  text generation
406 logic  spatial reasoning
455 translating visuals
527 cultural understanding
top_comments:
absolutely mindblowing the amount of understanding the model exhibits here is way way beyond anything else
im glad to see google back in the game this looks next level
very impressive want to try it
fyi this is embellished a bit its still extremely cool and impressive and i am so excited to see these advances but theres a fair amount they have to do to get to this exact state in a viral video demonstrating geminis capabilities google took significant artistic license it showed a user speaking with gemini but was actually representing a text conversation it showed a moving video but was feeding gemini still images it showed fast responses but sped those up it showed tight model outputs but shortened them for brevity it showed brief prompts eliciting terrific answers but listed longer prompts in a blog post  from big technlology by alex kantrowitz
the realtime element is by far the most impressive these sorts of asynchronous interactions are what ai has been missing thus far
just one problem the video isnt real we created the demo by capturing footage in order to test geminis capabilities on a wide range of challenges then we prompted gemini using still image frames from the footage and prompting via text parmy olsen at bloomberg was the first to report the discrepancy
that is incredibly impressive there were clearly some hidden prompts as it kept understanding switching contexts but still it was highly impressive

its truly fascinating to see what ai is now capable of

fascinating  i cant wait to see what weve accomplished in another 5 years
this has a lot of potential as an ai workbench for your child to replace their entire education from kindergarten to university

video_title: cillian murphy  margot robbie  actors on actors
tags: Variety,Variety Studio,cillian murphy,margot robbie,barbie,oppenheimer,cilian murphy,margot robbie cillian murphy,barbenheimer
description:
the barbenheimer phenomenon personified cillian murphy oppenheimer  margot robbie barbie discuss the experience of being the biggest summer box office sensation since avengers and what it was like working with christopher nolan and greta gerwig

variety actors on actors presented by amazon studiosmgm

httpbitlyvarietysubscribe

httpwwwfacebookcomvariety
httpwwwinstagramcomvariety
httpwwwtwittercomvariety
top_comments:
barbenheimer taking over the summer was something the world needed two completely different movies bringing people together
the person who paired them up deserves a raise
its so rare to see cillian murphy enjoying an interview and i am all in for it
apparently it was cillians team that reached out to variety asking for the pairing and i find that super wholesome
audiences dont like being told you should see this or you should see that they will decide and they will generate the interest themselves  such a brilliant quote
cillian doesnt look like he hates life in this how delightful it is to see him smile and laugh through the conversation he initiated this pairing and wanted to be there please give him more chances to make his own choices the result is seeing him truly happy to engage with someone
can we take a moment to appreciate that the producers even matched the microphones to the outfits 
it feels so good to see a fulllengthconversationalinterview being given by cilian could totally relate with margot when she started talking and asking questions about peaky blinders 
i love how he just ask her questions and keeps her talking as a fellow introvert what a classic move
yall the way i was devouring every single bit of cillians talking only the fans know how precious is having him speaking so lightly and for such a long time that man never shows up anywhere he doesnt have social media its a suffering to love him
margot is a masterclass on how to combine beauty and brains her insights on being a producer are so interesting as she was involved in the entire process from day one
i love how margot doesnt let cillian get away with his modest attitude and really grills him in a charming way on subjects like his apparent unawareness of the memes and the reasons why nolan loves to work with him

you can really sense that shes 100 authentic and doesnt shy away from confidently stating that she knew that the movie was going to be a hit and that her performance was influential in convincing matell
it brought so much joy to watch these two discovering each others role so natural and calm energy and its so amazing to see them being engaged to their characters
i just love how natural cillian is no vanity nothing fake no facade just him pure and simple its really calming listening to him
i love 2341 where margot is talking about their morning dance parties and how fun it is a cillian is just like ahhh bc he was in an artistic black hole doing this dark movie ive seen other actors from oppenheimer saying that they were having the best time and murphy had to be focused and couldntdidnt join in bc he was depriving himself of sleep and so zoned in and focused but his reaction to her saying how much fun it was made me laugh 
the fact that margot is cillians biggest fan makes this even better  loved this pairing and this convo
the reference about the phd woman who cant introspect is pure genius from greta impressive association to make with a barbie character wow
the barbenheimer phenomenon was so crazy usually when two big movies come out simultaneously one suffers greatly but in this case both movie actually helped the other movie succeed evm more
hands down the best actors on actors interview ever cillian and margot are such gems in themselves so coming together for this thoughtful back and forth was so special my first time actually getting through an entire aoa episode 3
cillian and margots dynamic is one where you would think it would be something so odd because of how almost paradoxal it is but this interview with them paired together honestly couldnt have worked out better both of them are so humble and grounded in their respective crafts and it was so easy to just sit and admire them for who they are

description:
gav cranks up the fastest phantom to show the simple yet fascinating approach to shooting ducks on your telly in the mid 80s 
instagram  httpswwwinstagramcomtheslowmoguys
filmed at up to 1750000 with the phantom tmx 7510
how the nintendo zapper worked in slow motion  the slow mo guys
top_comments:
i really want to see the laser scanner at a grocery store checkout  it seems to have mirrors moving very fast
i assume it flashes the boxes in two different frames so it can know which one you hit otherwise it wouldnt be able to tell which of the boxes youre aiming at
id love to see an inkjet printer in slowmotion i think the ink droplets falling on paper would be interesting
i love these quieter informative videos you do gav im glad youve kept them going after the lockdowns theyre fascinating
this continues to be magic how they figured out they could do this is unfathomable
so creative i love how when a technology is less developed creators are forced to use ingenuity and you get so many interesting things instead of twelve versions of the same thing
this game was a gem of my childhood once you discover the second controller can control the ducks its a whole new game
as a 37 year old now i was always curious how this worked and i also noticed the whole screen flashing on the menu really cool video
this is genuinely ahead of its time so much thinking and programming went even to make sure you wont cheat by pointing it at a white bulb not to mention nobody back then had slowmo cameras to even figure this out do more such smaller but super intriguing videos man
would really love to see the droplets from an inkjet printer 
that bit of filming the crt at super slomo alone is worth this video incredible stuff
this stuff is so amazing i live seeing how things from my childhood worked thank you
the reason it shows two white boxes on separate frames is so that it can tell which duck you shot at because whether it sees the first or second frame determines which duck it was
absolutely fascinating  i was total duck hunt maniac back in 80s and also obsessed about how things work  thank you so much for this slomo retrospective 
if you had a second crt on a channel that wasnt broadcasting static  snow and shot at it it was always a hit
this truly is brilliant i never would have guessed thats how it worked
this is so fascinating that i want to tell this to my grandkids how real engineering was done back in the days but i am afraid i am gonna forget it by then any tips to remember such a cool thing
i really like these how it works style of video there is so much technology that we take for granted that do amazing things in the blink of an eye
one thing people my friends at least didnt notice in duck hunt was that while in two player mode you could control the ducks movement with the controller while the other player was playing my friends would get frustrated that there ducks would move a lot more then mine would and id tell them theyre imagining it
so thats how it works i always wondered about that thanks for sharing this with us
